title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Stir sugar, salt, allspice, cinnamon, soda and flour together. Whisk eggs, oil, pumpkin and milk together.
Make a well in flour; add the pumpkin and egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Stir until moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and put in bottom of dish. Mix butter, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip. Spread half on top of crushed wafers. Cut up bananas and put on top of mixture. Add pineapple. Spread other half of mixture on and top with strawberries.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix melted butter and crushed pretzels in an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 5 minutes; let cool.

title: italian white bean soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onions in olive oil until tender. Add water, crushed tomatoes, bouillon cubes, peas and beans. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium and let simmer for 5 minutes.
Add beans and cook for 1 minute more or until heated through.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: banana nut chocolate chip bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pan. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream margarine.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture and banana alternately in 3 parts, starting and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Spoon into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Turn out of pan to cool.

title: cheddar puff
directions: Spread bread with soft butter and cut into cubes.
Put 1/3 of bread into 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1/3 cheese over bread. Repeat 2 more layers.
Beat all other ingredients and pour over bread and cheese.
Cover and chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
We always have this Christmas morning.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets into smaller than bite sized pieces. Cut off the tough outer layer of the stalk
and chop the tender part into small pieces.
You need about 8 cups of broccoli.
Saute bacon in small skillet until crisp and set aside.
Slice onions lengthwise, then into julienne strips.
In a large bowl, combine broccoli, bacon, onion strips and raisins.
In a small bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, sugar, pepper and vinegar.
Combine dressing with the vegetables and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Mix once before serving.
Try with the sunflower seeds.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fish cakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a bowl. Cover and refrigerate 10 minutes.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Stir ingredients until they are coated well.
Cover in a tight container.
Will last for several weeks.

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil until fluffy.
Add zucchini, flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Stir in pineapple, raisins and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg and dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: simple peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar and egg. Add 1 cup peanut butter. Use small size cookie baller. Put on ungreased cookie sheet. Top each cookie with a chocolate star; press down lightly. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 3 dozen plus 2 cookies.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13 pan, pour crushed pineapple. Do not drain. Spread pie filling over pineapple. Pour dry cake mix over pie filling. Sprinkle nuts over dry cake mix. Pour melted butter over top. Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. In bowl, mash bananas (you should have 1 cup).
Beat in sugar, then egg and butter.
In another bowl, stir together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to banana mixture and stir just until all flour is moistened.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: coleslaw
directions: Yield:
1 serving.
Carbohydrate 2 g, protein 0 g, fat 0 g, calories 8. One serving = l food exchange.

title: spoon burgers on buns
directions: In large skillet, saute onion, celery and bell pepper in oil until tender (5 minutes).
Add beef; cook and stir until meat is browned; drain.
Stir in cheese, tomato sauce, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire and salt.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Serve in buns. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Cook sugar, buttermilk and soda in 3-quart saucepan to soft ball stage (234° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and add vanilla and pecan halves.
Beat until candy thickens.
Will be ready quick.
Drop on waxed paper.
Makes approximately 20 small pralines.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Grease a large pie or quiche pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 40 to 45 minutes.
Top will turn brown.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Stew rhubarb first.
Cook rhubarb.
Put in one package Jell-O. Cook a few minutes.

title: snow pudding(sne pudding)
directions: Pour into a small bowl 1/2 cup cold water; sprinkle the gelatin evenly over cold water.
Let stand for 5 minutes to soften.
Blend softened gelatin into the hot water.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Stir in sugar and lemon juice until dissolved.
Chill in refrigerator until slightly thicker than unbeaten egg white. Stir occasionally.
Lightly oil a 2 1/2-quart fancy mold with salad oil.
Set it aside to drain.
When gelatin is of desired consistency, beat until frothy.
Beat the egg whites until rounded peaks are formed and whites do not slide when bowl is partially inverted.
Gently fold gelatin mixture into beaten egg whites. Turn into mold and chill until firm (at least 4 hours).
Serve with Vanilla Sauce.

title: wendy mccurdy's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until well-blended.
Blend eggs and sugar.
Heat milk over low heat, add eggs and sugar.
(Cook in heavy pan, stirring constantly until it thickens or coats metal spoon.)
Do not scald or boil.
Add whipping cream and vanilla as you pour into freezer.
Pour into freezer, not too full because it swells. Divide recipe in half for 1/2 gallon freezer.

title: elvis presley salad
directions: Mix both jellos with 1 cup hot water.
Add both cokes, pineapple, nuts, cream cheese, cherries, and mix well.
Chill.

title: hot spiced fruit
directions: Drain all fruit.
Fruit should be as dry as possible.
Mix melted butter, sugar and spices with fruit.
Microwave at Full power for 6 minutes.
Stir fruit and drain as necessary.
Add additional butter and cinnamon to taste.

title: double pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool on rack.
Use the recipe for "Pistachio Fluffy Frosting," in this cookbook to frost the cake.

title: hidden valley cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients. Shape into ball. Roll in nuts. Chill before serving.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Put a cup of the flour in a shallow bowl.
Make an indent with your fingers; break 1 egg into the dent, add a shake of salt to egg and mix with a fork to gather the flour into the egg.
Do this until you can use your fingers to roll and knead the egg sponge you have made.
Knead the sponge until it is firm and not sticky. Roll out on a flat surface with flour sprinkled on it.
Cut into strips as wide as you like.
I use a pizza cutter for this.
Do this with each egg.
Use more flour as needed.
You can dry the noodles or drop them as is into boiling stock and simmer for 1 hour, covered.

title: sweet and sour slaw(from jane brody, good food gourmet)
directions: Place the dressing ingredients in a blender and process them on low until they are well mixed.

title: ione's mexican casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion until done.
Drain.
Stir in all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: never fail or angel biscuits
directions: Mix together water, yeast and sugar. When yeast dissolves, add salad oil, buttermilk, baking soda, salt and flour. Cover; let stand in the refrigerator for awhile or overnight (good for a week). Form into biscuits by rolling on floured surface or by hand. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: refrigerator roll dough(for rolls or coffee cakes)
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup water (110°) with 1 teaspoon of the sugar.
Combine milk, sugar, salt and lemon rind.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and well beaten eggs; mix.
Add 1/2 of the flour; mix and add margarine.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour and mix, but do not knead.
Dough will be sticky.
Place in greased bowl; chill.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring butter,
cocoa and water to boil in saucepan.
Beat eggs, milk, flour, sugar, vanilla, vinegar and soda in bowl.
Add heated mixture.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jezebel
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cream cheese) well.
Store in refrigerator.
Pour over Philadelphia cream cheese cakes and serve with crackers.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute vegetables in butter in a pot large enough to hold all ingredients.
Add rice and stock.
Stir.
After 5 minutes, add raisins and stir again.
Cook slowly, covered, for 10 minutes until rice is tender.
Add almonds, season and serve.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: best hush puppies
directions: Mix together meal, flour, sugar, egg, onion and buttermilk. Add water to thin.
Deep-fry.

title: beef spread
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together and let stand while mixing together rest of ingredients.
Mix all ingredients.
Add dried onion and wine.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: jello toss
directions: Mix fruit and cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with dry Jell-O (about 1 tablespoon).
Toss salad until Jell-O is dissolved and salad is pink color.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, blend soup mix with water.
Bring to a boil, then continue boiling, stirring occasionally, 1 minute or until slightly thickened.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Cook, uncovered, stirring frequently, 5 minutes or until chicken is done and vegetables are tender.
Serve over hot rice.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a 9-inch pie shell. Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to moderate (350°) and bake for 35 to 40 minutes longer or until a silver knife inserted in center of filling comes out clean.
Let cool before serving.

title: spiced pretzels
directions: Break pretzels into pieces.
Coat with oil mixed with other ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish at 400° for 15 minutes. Cool on baking sheet.

title: pork hawaiian
directions: Marinate the pork in the pineapple juice and wine (or rum) for about 3 hours.
Cover with pineapple, oranges and pimentos.
Cook according to weight of pork, at about 350°.

title: clam chowder
directions: Dice 1 large potato; boil in water and clam juice from can of clams.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Add clams, diced onion, butter, salt and pepper and half and half.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley. Cover and let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt oleo, brown sugar and Karo syrup.
Boil for 2 minutes. Add the baking soda; beat in.
Put the popcorn in paper grocery sack.
Pour sauce over; shake well.
Close bag; put in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes, then shake.
Do this 3 to 4 times. Test cooled kernels for crispness.

title: pork chops with hawaiian rice
directions: Sprinkle the pork chops with salt and pepper and brown in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: apple pie
directions: You can use jelly roll pan or use tart pans.
Line pan with pastry.
I usually buy the Pillsbury pie crust in the box. You can make your own if you want.
Make sure you roll it out very thin. Spread red jam in thin layer over pastry.
I use strawberry. Spread cake dough over jam.
Bake until cake is done. Frost with powdered sugar and water icing with almond flavoring.

title: shoo-fly pie(amish)
directions: Sift together and cut in margarine, the dry ingredients as for pie crust; stir in molasses, water and soda; pour into the unbaked pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 425° and 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned pot roast
directions: Cut roast in half; brown in a Dutch oven in oil on all sides. Sprinkle with pepper.
Place the carrots, onion and garlic in a 5-quart slow cooker; top with the roast.
In a bowl, combine the tomato sauce, wine or broth, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings; pour over roast.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat and keep warm.
Skim fat from cooking juices; pour into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
In a small bowl, combine the cornstarch and water until smooth; stir into cooking juices.
Return to a boil; cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes or until thickened.
Serve with sliced beef.
Yield:
12 to 14 servings.

title: hawaii cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Combine liquids and mix with dry ingredients until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in ungreased 9 x 11-inch or 9-inch pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until tender; reserve broth.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth according to package directions.
Saute onion, green pepper, mushrooms and garlic in oil.
Debone chicken and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Combine chicken, sauteed vegetables, stewed tomatoes, soup and pepper.
Mix well and stir in cheese.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: cleaned-up dirt cake
directions: With mixer, beat cream cheese and sugar together.
In another bowl, combine milk and pudding; whip the wire whisk or mixer until smooth.
Add whipped topping to pudding; mix well.
Stir together both mixtures.
In food processor, process cookies until they're fine crumbs (or crush manually).

Line each flower pot with plastic wrap or foil; begin layering cookie crumbs with pudding mixture, making several layers, starting and ending with cookies. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours.
If desired, garnish with flower and gummy worms before serving. Makes 12 servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs for about 3 minutes.
Add melted margarine, sugar, flour, salt, milk and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into buttered 10-inch glass pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
(Do not use pie crust.)

title: ladyfinger delight
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Line sides and bottom of spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Beat together cream cheese and heavy cream.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Keep beating until thick.
Pour mixture into pan.
Add a layer of ladyfingers.
Pour rest of mixture in; pour cherries on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: creole bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar.
Add milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Mix thoroughly.
Add bread and raisins and let set 15 minutes before pouring into 9 x 13-inch pan or a 4-quart baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
This is yummy!

title: upside-down stuffed peppers
directions: To brown meat, crumble ground beef into microwave-safe colander.
Add onion and celery.
Place colander over 1 3/4 quart casserole dish.
Cook, covered, on 100% power for 5 to 7 minutes, or until meat is browned, and vegetables are tender, stirring once.
Remove colander.
Drain grease from casserole dish and wipe out.
Transfer meat mixture to casserole dish.
Stir in tomatoes, 1/2 cup of cheese, uncooked rice, worcestershire sauce and Italian seasoning.
Quarter peppers and arrange, cut side down, on top of meat mixture.
Cover, and cook on 100% power for 9 to 12 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese before serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix hot water and strawberry jello.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Pour 1/2 of this in bowl and let congeal.
Spread 1 carton sour cream over it, then pour rest of jello mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: one-dish spaghetti
directions: Brown beef lightly over moderate heat; drain off fat.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Cover and cook over high heat for about 5 minutes, stirring often.
Reduce heat and simmer about 30 minutes or until spaghetti is tender, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking to skillet.
Serve hot.

title: mango fruit parfait
directions: Reserve raspberries and 4 slices kiwi for garnish.
Put mangoes and orange juice in blender and puree until smooth. Slice 20 of the strawberries; leave 4 whole.
Line the bottom of 4 balloon wine glasses with the sliced strawberries.
Pour a thin layer of the mango over each to cover.
Layer kiwi on top of the puree.
Divide the rest of the mango puree among the glasses.
Top each with a slice of kiwi surrounded by raspberries.
Make a slit in each of the whole strawberries and position 1 on the rim of each glass.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate for 15 minutes.

title: nora did it pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: mother's dumplings
directions: Cut up chicken and boil until tender.
Salt broth to taste. Combine milk, eggs and salt.
Stir in flour and knead until it will not stick to hands.
Roll paper thin and cut into 1-inch strips.
Cook 15 minutes in chicken broth.

title: punch
directions: Cook sugar and water until it comes to a boil.
Let cool; add remaining ingredients.

title: rice with pecans
directions: In a medium size casserole with lid, melt the margarine in microwave.
Add the garlic powder and pecans.
Cover and heat 20 seconds.
Stir, then add rice, stir well.
Replace cover and heat 1 1/2 minutes or longer if rice is cold.

title: carolyn's oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Add oats and sugars.
Cut in shortening.
Blend in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 to 4 dozen.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Wash and peel mushrooms and dice.
Stir into the mushrooms, the stock (veal or chicken).
Thicken with flour that has been mixed with butter, salt and pepper until creamy.
At the last moment, add a bit of whipped cream or croutons.

title: kool-aid jelly
directions: Stir Kool-Aid mix with water until dissolved.
Mix Sure-Jell in separate small bowl with 1/2 cup sugar.
Gradually stir into Kool-Aid, mixing thoroughly.
Set aside 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining sugar gradually.
Continue to stir until completely dissolved and no longer grainy.
(Any small lumps will disappear after jelly stands overnight.)
Pour into clean, dry containers, filling to with 1/2-inch of tops.
Cover with tight lids.
Stand at room temperature overnight.
Store in freezer.
Refrigerate after opening.
Makes 4 (8 ounce) containers.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix altogether.
Put in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: special k loaf
directions: Mix well.
Put in casserole pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veggie squares
directions: Press out 1 can of crescent rolls onto an ungreased cookie sheet (approximately 9 x 12-inch).
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Repeat with other can. Cool completely. Combine softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix. Spread 1/2 on each baked crust.
Top layer with 1/2 carrots, broccoli, cauliflower and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the cheese.
Refrigerate.
Cut into 2 x 3 squares.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Saute in butter the onions, celery and pepper.
Mix together with all remaining ingredients, topping with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: liver lyonnaise
directions: Cut liver in 1 1/2-inch cubes. Blend flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Roll liver in flour mixture. Brown on all sides in hot fat in heavy skillet; remove liver from pan. Fry potatoes and onions in remaining fat until lightly browned and potatoes are tender. Alternate liver and potato-onion mixture in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine soup, milk, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper and pour over top. Cover; bake in moderate oven at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: orange fluff
directions: Heat all but Cool Whip to boiling.
Cool in refrigerator. When starting to set firm, add Cool Whip.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In large pot, cover chicken with water and boil slowly until tender.
Remove chicken to platter.
Add salt, pepper and margarine to broth.
Simmer to blend seasonings.

title: hot swiss onion dip
directions: Mix above ingredients together thoroughly.
Place in small baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and serve with your favorite dipping chips.
(Very good with O'Boise or Jones Marcelled chips.)

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onion and add chili and soup.
Heat and mix; season it.
Soften tortillas in hot grease and fill with meat and then add a little cream cheese; roll up and put remaining meat and Cheddar cheese on top.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add marshmallows to hot mixture.
Add soft cream cheese.
Cool.
Add undrained pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour in dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: boiled uncooked oat cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter, salt and milk to a rolling boil. Then cook for 3 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add raw oats, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts.
Mix and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: grilled italian sausages
directions: Mix herbs in bowl.
Crush by hand to release flavors.
Wash each sausage and pat dry.
Rub each sausage in herb mixture to coat.
Grill until done.

title: homemade cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add as much water or milk as desired.
More water or milk for moister cake, less for dryer.

title: spaghetti chili soup
directions: Cook spaghetti and onions until done in 1 1/2 quarts of water. Don't drain.
Add tomato soup and chili; stir in the salt and chili powder.
Cover and let simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10 to 15 minutes over medium heat.

title: reuben stuffed bread
directions: Chop corned beef into small pieces.
Shred Swiss cheese.
Mix all ingredients (except bread) well.
Cut off top of bread and pull out center.
Keep bread to dip.
Fill bread with mixture and replace top.
Triple wrap bread with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until cheese is melted and mixture is hot. Serve with crackers, party rye or breadsticks.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Clean chicken.
Pour marinade over chicken and let stand in frig for at least 3 hours, longer is better.

title: molded cucumber mousse
directions: Stir jello into
boiling
water.
Add
lemon
juice and salt. Refrigerate until
partially set.
Whip and add remaining ingredients. Pour into an 8-inch ring mold and refrigerate until set.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add other ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together.
Add oil, nuts, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to batter.
Mix until blended.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until cake shrinks from sides of pan.
Frost with powdered sugar glaze or put on Dream Whip.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Put head of cabbage in	freezer
for
about
1	hour or until the outside leaves start
to
freeze.
Peel off 8 leaves and let soften to room temperature.
Mix together ground beef, 1/2 cup tomato soup, rice
and
chopped onion, salt and pepper to taste. Spoon into cabbage leaves at stem end and fold over sides and roll up.
Secure
with a toothpick and lay stem side down in a large pan or
Dutch
oven, and add rest of soup with 3/4 cup water. Cook over medium heat for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel and core apples.
Cut into fourths.
Roll out biscuits and cut, forming 20 halves.
Roll biscuit half around apple wedge.
Place apples in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix water and sugar and heat until sugar melts.
Pour over apples.
Melt 2 sticks margarine and pour over apples. Sprinkle cinnamon and bake 1 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots for 5 minutes, then drain and cool.
Mix other ingredients in a bowl.
Add carrots.
Chill to blend flavors. Serve over salad greens.

title: pool gogi - korean dish
directions: Combine all ingredients except meat.
Then add meat and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 2 hours.
Put a little sesame oil in a frypan and get hot.
Then pour meat mixture into pan and stir-fry until done.
Serve over rice.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda, sugar, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add shortening and mix.
Add beaten egg to mixture and mix.
Add rolled oats and mashed bananas and mix.
Drop by teaspoonful on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mammy lou's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased skillet. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Mix water and sugar together; bring to a boil.
Let cool slightly.
Mix all fruit together.
Pour sugar water over fruit; mix together.
Freeze overnight.
Take out of freezer an hour before serving.

title: layered enchiladas
directions: Cook green peppers and onion in a small amount of oil.
Add hamburger; cook.
Drain meat before adding cumin powder and salt. Pour enchilada sauce in saucepan and heat.
Dip tortillas in sauce and layer tortillas, meat and Velveeta slices.
Pour any remaining sauce over layers and heat.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add sugar and peanut butter and mix well.
Add 1/2 bowl of Cool Whip; mix.
Pour into a graham cracker crust or prebaked pie shell.
Add the rest of the Cool Whip as topping for the pie.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Put everything in your crock-pot and cook until done or put in oven at 375° and cook until tender.
Makes delicious sandwiches!

title: green and white salad
directions: Dry thawed frozen peas with paper towel, also broccoli and cauliflower.
Mix dressing ingredients (last 5 ingredients).
I like to use a garlic press with fresh garlic.
Combine dressing with vegetables.
A great salad to make ahead of time, even day before.
Keeps well several days if there are leftovers.

title: gourmet cheese dip
directions: Saute meats and onion.
Melt soup, Ro-Tel and Velveeta cheese. Mix meat mixture and cheese mixture.
Serve as a dip or over spaghetti.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure.
Add baking powder and sift again. Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually; cream.
Add beaten egg, then flour alternately with milk.
Beat in heavy skillet.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Add 1 cup brown sugar.
Stir until melted. Add 1 cup pineapple or enough slices to cover bottom of skillet (or peaches or apricots).
Place cherry in the center of each slice, if desired.
Pour batter over mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Pour in baking dish.
Add crushed Ritz crackers and butter on the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate dream
directions: Melt chocolate chips, cool.
Stir in beaten egg yolks.
Fold in whipped heavy cream.
Fold chocolate mixture into egg whites.
Line sides and bottom of spring pan with ladyfingers.
Gently pour chocolate mixture into pan.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: cranberry and sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve
jello
in 2 cups boiling water. Add cranberry sauce and
chill until syrupy.
Carefully swirl in sour cream and nuts. Serves 8.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Very good.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Stir the first 3 ingredients together; press in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: red trader punch
directions: Combine lemon and orange juice and grenadine syrup; pour over block of ice to chill.
Just before serving, pour ginger ale down side of bowl.
Add lemon slices, berries or sliced fruit in season.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: angel salad
directions: Add all together.
Add extra toppings and green grapes on top if desired.

title: fruit dip
directions: Can also use Tang or Kool-Aid.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Dissolve chicken soup in 1/2 cup water.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with rosemary.
Bake for about 30 minutes.

title: simple persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into well-greased pan. Bake 1 hour in moderate oven at 300° to 325°.

title: butterscotch fingers
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan and cool.
Add brown sugar.
Stir until blended. Add the egg and vanilla.
Stir well.
Sift flour and baking powder into butter mixture.
Stir well.
The mixture will be stiff.
Spread evenly in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Mix sugar and vinegar together and pour over ingredients. Mix and let set for 24 hours. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: boiled beef with horseradish sauce
directions: Cook beef a day in advance of serving.
Place meat in kettle; add just enough water to cover.
Add onion, carrot and seasonings. Cover and simmer 3 to 4 hours, or until meat is tender.
Let meat stand in broth 24 hours to absorb flavor.
Reheat meat in broth. Yields 8 portions.

title: apple cinnamon pancakes
directions: Prepare pancake mix according to package directions.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and apples.
Stir into batter.
Cook on hot, greased skillet until browned on both sides.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Cream sugar, melted butter and eggs, mixing well.
Add flour, cocoa and salt; mix well.
Stir in vanilla and nutmeats.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until set.
Serve with whipped topping and strawberries.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all together in blender. Turn on for 10 seconds at a time. Pour into a buttered glass pie pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carpet cleaner(helpful hint)
directions: Mix cornmeal and Borax together.
Sprinkle mixture on carpet. Leave on for 1 hour.
Vacuum thoroughly.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Fold in blueberries (frozen can be used).
Use paper-lined crinkle cups, fill 1/2 full and bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ladyfinger sticks
directions: Whip the cream and add the apricot jam.
Split ladyfingers, fill with whipped cream mixture and dust top with powdered sugar.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onions, celery and carrots in butter until tender. Cook potatoes in water with chicken bouillon cubes. Cook until tender. Add onions, celery and carrots. Add fresh parsley and salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil bouillon cubes, water, celery, carrots, potatoes and onions for 20 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables.
Cook until tender, about 10 or 15 minutes.
Add soup and 1/2 cup water and cheese. Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer water and raisins until raisins are plump.
Drain raisins.
Reserve water.
Add water to make 1/2 cup.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in reserved liquid. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop rounded teaspoonful of dough on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until light brown at 400°.
Yields 6 1/2 dozen.

title: mango juice with a punch
directions: Mix ingredients in punch bowl.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine with sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in wafer crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Spread batter in greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then invert on wire rack to cool.
Yields 12 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients in 2-quart bowl.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 50 minutes, or until firm.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: italian cole slaw
directions: Bring to a boil vinegar, salad oil, 2 tablespoons sugar, salt, dry mustard and celery seed.
Pour over cabbage and cover.
Let stand about 24 hours before serving.

title: kona inn banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar thoroughly.
Add
bananas and eggs. Sift dry ingredients; blend into
creamed
mixture, but do not overmix.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350°
for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 2 (1 1/2-pound) loaves.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Gradually add salad oil.
Sift flour, salt, and soda. Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and poppy seed.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: salted pecans
directions: Melt butter with Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle over pecans in a shallow dish.
Sprinkle with other ingredients.
Stir and toast in oven at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir every few minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook in crock-pot.
Finally add 1 can clams.
Heat thoroughly. Serves 4.

title: creamy crab and artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
In medium mixing bowl, blend together the cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients and place mixture in a glass pie plate.
Bake uncovered for 15-18 min. until heated through and lightly browned. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook asparagus or broccoli; drain.
Arrange in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Blend soup, Worcestershire sauce and nutmeg. Pour half over asparagus.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of the cheese.
Top with chicken and remaining soup mixture.
Sprinkle with another 1/3 of the cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until heated through (about 20 minutes).
Whip the cream until soft peaks form.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Spread mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Broil 3 to 4-inches from the heat until golden (1 to 2 minutes).
Serves 6.

title: blueberry roly poly
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add enough milk to mixture to make a stiff dough.
Pat dough out on a floured board in oblong shape.
Put berries on dough (I like to sprinkle with sugar) and roll up like a jelly roll.
Pinch ends together. Seal real well.
Place into pan with about 1 inch water.
Use large enough pan as roll will double in size.
Cover with lid. Bake at 350° until done.
Sprinkle outside with sugar.
Eat, enjoy and remember.

title: spaghetti(use 9 x 15-inch dish)
directions: Cook spaghetti and put on bottom of 9 x 15-inch dish.
Place on top of this the cheese.
Brown hamburger, hot sausage, onion and garlic together.
Add tomato sauce, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, basil and salt and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes. Pour over cheese and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
This freezes great!
I make 2 dishes (9 x 9-inch) and I freeze one!

title: rice with mushrooms
directions: Melt butter; saute onions for 2 minutes.
Drain mushrooms.
Add to onion.
Also add 2 cups of rice.
Brown for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add water, bouillon and pepper; bring to a boil, then reduce to simmer with lid on until it absorbs liquid (20 minutes).
Add salt, if needed.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; let stand for 20 minutes. Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients; beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in oatmeal.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Roll crackers to make crumbs.
Mix all ingredients together and cook 25 minutes at 300°. This makes 1 pie.

title: treasure puffs
directions: Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place a piece of candy on each triangle.
Wrap dough around candy, completely covering it. Pinch edges of dough tightly to seal.
Dip each roll in melted butter.
Place on baking sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°. Serve warm.

title: skillet green beans
directions: Fry bacon in electric skillet, crumble.
Add green beans, onion, tomatoes, tomato juice and a little crushed red pepper. Cook about an hour at 350°.

title: grandma's coffee cookies
directions: Beat shortening until fluffy.
Beat in sugar.
Next, beat in eggs and salt; add coffee.
Mix together flour, soda and baking powder.
Add water alternately with flour mixture. Add chips, raisins, nuts or coconut.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheets. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375° to 400°.

title: monterey bake
directions: Saute meat in skillet until done.
Drain.
Add garlic and onion powder.
Blend salt, Tabasco, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Add this mixture and remaining ingredients, except corn chips, to ground beef.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with corn chips. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spanish meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine beef, onion, salt, steak sauce, 5 tablespoons ketchup and cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place into shallow pan and bake for 10 minutes.

title: potatoes with cheese
directions: Butter a casserole and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Drain potatoes.
Layer 1 can of potatoes in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Layer the other can of potatoes on next, then the rest of the cheese.
Sprinkle a little salt and pepper to taste in the milk and pour the milk over the mixture.
Cover and microwave 15 minutes.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Spray a 7 x 11 glass baking dish with non-stick cooking spray.
Sprinkle uncooked rice in bottom of dish.
Place tomato slices in bottom of dish.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix well in large pitcher. Serve chilled.

title: classic california avocado guacamole
directions: Using fork, coarsely mash avocados with lemon juice and garlic.
Stir in remaining ingredients to blend.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: raisin bars
directions: Cook or simmer first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add egg to cooked raisins mixture.
Mix the raisin mixture with the other ingredients.
Spread on a jelly roll type pan and bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: jalapeno cheese log
directions: Roll softened Velveeta into a ball; lay between 2 pieces of wax paper and spread it until it is about 1/2-inch thick.
Mix cream cheese with peppers and onions.
Spread on Velveeta.	Roll cheese jelly roll fashion using wax paper.	Press ends of cheese roll together and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Spread chilled pepper jelly on top; slice and serve with wheat crackers.

title: donuts
directions: Add flour and knead.
Let rise for 1 hour in greased bowl. (Cover.)
Knead again and cut out donuts; let rise for 1 more hour in warm place.
Cook in hot grease until brown.

title: 3 minute microwave fudge
directions: Melt margarine on High for 1 minute (will not be totally melted).
Add powdered sugar, crunchy peanut butter, vanilla and cocoa at the same time.
Micro on High for 2 minutes.
Take out and stir until fudgy.
Pour in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan. Refrigerate; when hard, cut into small squares and serve.

title: cherry torte
directions: In a bowl mix first 4 ingredients, then firmly pack into a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Spread cherry pie filling over crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, whipped cream or serve plain.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Clean and cut chicken in servings.
Melt butter in roaster and add flour.
Let it brown, then add chicken and seasonings.
Partly cover chicken with water.
Cover the roaster and cook in a 450° oven until tender; lower the oven temperature to 300° and cook until well done.
Add more water if needed.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes, cut in halves.
Cook bacon and melt butter while preparing potatoes.
Keep oven on.
Spoon out potatoes from shells, leaving only enough to keep skin firm.
Spoon in 1/2 teaspoon butter, bacon and mushrooms; then top with Cheddar or your choice of cheese.
Serve with sour cream, ketchup, mustard or horseradish sauce.

title: easy peach delight
directions: Combine pie filling and peaches (with syrup) in baking dish. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of this.
Pour melted butter on top of dry cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: millie's noodles
directions: Mix together and roll out.
Let dry, then cut.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Beat the egg whites and milk together.
Then combine sugar, flour and cocoa together and stir into egg mixture.
Stir carefully to dissolve lumps.
Microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes. Stir every 2 to 3 minutes.
When done, add butter and vanilla, stirring well.
Pour into pie shell and cool.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Melt butter. Stir into crushed chocolate wafers.
Use for crust (press into 8-inch pie pan).
Melt marshmallows in milk. Cool.
Stir in creme de menthe and creme de cacao.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pie shell.
Garnish with cherries and chocolate on top.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: captain's punch
directions: Combine lemonade, orange juice, sugar, bitters and rum in punch bowl.
Mix.
Place a large block of ice in punch bowl.
Add carbonated water.
Stir well.
Garnish with fruit slices.
Serves 24.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg until creamy.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk; beat until smooth.
Fold in rhubarb and add vanilla last.
Sprinkle on top before baking 1/2 cup white sugar, mixed with 1 teaspoon cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, tomatoes, onion powder and garlic powder together and set aside.
Lay bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan with Doritos and chicken; then pour broth over and add onion and green pepper.
Add 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Pour soup mixture over and bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
About 5 minutes before done, add rest of cheese.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Kisses, in large bowl.
Shape dough in balls; roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine yolks, milk and oil; stir into dry ingredients.
Fold in whites. Bake.

title: mushroom noodles
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Drain noodles.
Add can of mushroom soup and 1/4 stick butter.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Blend first 9 ingredients together.
Add oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 12 minutes (9 minutes for chewy; 12 minutes for crispy).
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; place on wire rack.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix bouillon cubes in water well; stir in potatoes, celery, onions, salt and garlic.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Cool and add cream cheese, blending well.
Return to stove and simmer to reheat.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Mix all in a large casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° to 350°.
Remove from oven and top with 1 can chow mein noodles. Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: chili beans with deer meat
directions: Fry meat in 1/2 cup of oil until done.
Add pinto beans; drain oil.
Add green peppers and onions; fry until almost done on low heat.
Add beans and black pepper.
Mix Chili-O in a small bowl with a small amount of cold water.
Add to ingredients; cook on low heat with lid for 20 minutes to mix flavors.
(Make sure to mix Chili-O in a bowl; that way, it will not cause lumps.)

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion, celery and pimento in oleo.
Add soup and cooked spaghetti.
Place in casserole dish and stir in cheese and chicken.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: beef rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add carrots, peas, 2 cups water, salt and pepper to meat.
Heat 5 minutes; stir rice into meat and vegetable mixture.
Bring to a boil; lower heat, cover and cook 20 minutes or until rice is tender and fluffy.
With last cup of flour and water, make a paste.
Add to rice mixture; cook 5 minutes and serve.
Yields 8 servings.

title: strawberry sour cream mold
directions: Make Jell-O.
Add fruit and nuts.
Pour half of Jell-O into mold and let set.
Leave other half out of refrigerator.
Pour sour cream on top of set Jell-O.
Pour remaining Jell-O on top and refrigerate until set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: garden vegetable mix
directions: Shred enough of the cabbage to make 6 to 8 cups.
Stem green beans and cut them into 1-inch pieces.
Combine all ingredients in a large kettle or Dutch oven.
Fill sink with ice water.
Cook vegetables to a full boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat. Cool quickly by setting kettle in sink of ice water.
Put vegetable mix into 4 (1-quart) containers, leaving 1/2-inch space at top. Seal and label container Garden Vegetable Mix. Freeze and use within 6 months.
Makes about 15 cups of mix.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Preheat wok pot; add oil to bottom.
When hot, place sliced garlic in pot and heat.
May remove if desired.
Cook onion, bacon, shrimp, mushrooms, peas and carrots, stir-frying often. Add rice to wok.
Stir-fry until well mixed with vegetables.
Add soya sauce as desired.

title: oven french toast
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan in hot oven.	Add brown sugar and cinnamon; mix well.
Cut bread into 1-inch squares. Place bread into the pan over mixture.
Beat eggs with milk.
Pour over bread.
Chill, tightly covered, in refrigerator overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with warm syrup and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Yields 12 servings. Approximately 250 calories per serving.

title: german green beans
directions: Saute onion and bacon.
Drain green beans and add to mixture. Add stewed tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, dissolve bouillon in 2 cups of water (simmer cubes in the water on stove). Add bouillon to onion mixture.
Mix cornstarch into 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to mixture.
Simmer until heated thoroughly and mixture thickens.

title: microwave mints
directions: Put
butter
and milk in a 2 quart microwaveproof bowl. Cook on
High
(Maximum Power) for 45 seconds, or until butter is melted.
Stir in frosting mix.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes
or
until
bubbly.
Stir
twice
during cooking time. Stir in
food coloring to tint.
Add extract.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls
onto
waxed paper.
When cool, store in airtight container.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: Sprinkle
meat	tenderizer,
pepper,
salt and thyme on beef. Turn
meat	several
times	to coat evenly.
In roaster oven,
or large Corning dish, cook, uncovered, in oven at 400° for
1 hour to brown, turning only once.
Add remaining ingredients,
stirring thoroughly.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda and cinnamon into a large bowl. Make a well in center of flour mixture.
In another bowl, mix together strawberries and juice, oil, pecans and eggs. Pour strawberry mixture into well in flour mixture.
Mix together slowly, but thoroughly.
Pour batter into well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Yields 2 loaves.

title: baked seafood salad
directions: Early in the day, cut shrimp in halves lengthwise, or break in halves crosswise.
Flake crab meat.
Combine and add green pepper, onion, celery, mayonnaise, Worcestershire, salt and pepper; mix lightly.
Spread in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion and celery in oil with garlic salt to taste until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, sugar, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with about 1 tablespoon cold water.
Add to pan and cook until thick.
Add shrimp and green peppers.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: george's chocolate rum balls
directions: Melt chocolate bits over hot water.
Add corn syrup and bourbon or substitute.
Combine vanilla wafer crumbs, powdered sugar and nuts.
Add chocolate mixture.
(If cream is used, add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.)
Let stand 30 minutes.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated or powdered sugar.
Let ripen in covered container at least 3 days.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to 325°.
Put pan in cold water.
Add peanut butter to taste.
Beat until getting stiff.
Pour in buttered pan and put in freezer to cool (approximately 15 to 20 minutes).

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Mix cheese and soup in saucepan.
Melt gelatine in water and add.
Stir in onion and shrimp; remove from heat.
Fold in the mayonnaise.
Pour into mold.
Chill for 24 hours.
Serve with buttery crackers.

title: butterscotch chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl, add eggs, oil, water and pudding mix to cake mix. Beat thoroughly. Mix in sour cream. Bake per instructions on cake mix box.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Combine caramels and evaporated milk on top of double boiler. Stir mixture until melted.
Combine cake mix, remaining milk and softened margarine.
Blend until mixture holds together.
Stir in walnuts (optional).
Press half of the cake mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove pan from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Pour melted caramels evenly over the chips.
Crumble remaining cake mixture over caramels and bake again at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry the bacon and reserve drippings. Drain bacon on paper towel. Saute the onions in 1 tablespoon bacon drippings. Combine the bacon, onions, celery, carrots, flour, salt, potatoes, pepper and milk. Cook, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Stir occasionally. Bring to boil, then add clams. Cook 5 minutes more.

title: layered salad
directions: Chop the head of lettuce for first layer.
Chop the purple onion and layer over lettuce.
Chop the cauliflower.
Layer the cheese over the cauliflower.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and pepper. Stir well, then spread over cheese.
Fry the bacon and crumble it up over the salad.
When serving, make sure that each person receives all layers.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Mix bread, onions, celery and seasonings in a large bowl.
Add eggs and butter and mix well.
If mixture seems too dry, add more broth to moisten but do not make pastry.
Put in a greased baking pan or muffin pans.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: western broccoli salad
directions: Place 1 inch of water and broccoli in a skillet and bring to a boil. Boil one minute, cover and remove from heat. Let stand
3 to 4 minutes or until
crisp-tender. Drain and pat dry. In a serving bowl toss broccoli, tomatoes, beans, onions, cheese and salt. Drizzle with ranch dressing. Toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate until ready to be served.

title: blondies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Generously grease an 8-inch square baking pan.
Melt the butter and add the brown sugar.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 30 seconds or until well blended.
Cool, then add the egg.

title: sweet cole slaw dressing
directions: Use 1/4 cup dressing to 1 cup shredded cabbage.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Important: Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Mix mustard with part of vinegar and make thin before adding to pot, mustard may lump otherwise.

title: bacon and potato soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and saute onions 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour off fat and add potatoes and water; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Stir in soup and sour cream; crumble bacon into pot.
Add milk, salt, pepper and parsley.
Heat to serving temperature but do not boil (warm not hot).

title: microwave chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all but cheese in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover; cook on High 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top; cover and let stand for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Pour warm water into large mixing bowl; add yeast; let stand a few minutes; stir to dissolve.
Add sugar, salt, shortening, egg and half the flour.
Beat until smooth with mixer (medium speed) or by hand (1 1/2 to 2 minute).
Add remainder of flour and stir in by hand until flour is moistened and batter smooth, about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Scrape down batter from sides of bowl.
Cover bowl.
Let rise in warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Grease pans. Stir down batter in 20 to 25 strokes.
Make rolls.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream cheese and butter. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Press onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Transfer to wire rack to cool or serve warm.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and pour into 2 medium loaf pans which have been well-greased.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in pecans.
Pour melted butter into 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan. Spread pecan mixture over butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: judy's punch for all occasions
directions: Brew 1 tea bag in 4 cups hot water.
Add cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Add sugar.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water and add to tea mixture.
Mix well.
Add enough water to make 3-quarts.
Add pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill.
Serve cold.

title: angel biscuits (rolls)
directions: Mix as you would for biscuit dough, cutting shortening into flour, sugar, soda, salt, and baking powder, adding buttermilk and yeast last.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Place in refrigerator for cooling so that dough will be easier to handle. When you prepare the dough, you will find that you will have to add a lot of flour (dough is sticky).
Cut biscuits and dip or brush with melted butter.
Fold biscuits over and place in pan.
Bake in hot oven (400° or 425°).
Store unused dough in refrigerator.

title: cranberry salsa
directions: About 1 hour before serving or day ahead:
In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat with hot olive or salad oil, cook onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cranberries, brown sugar, salt and 2 tablespoons water.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring frequently, until cranberries pop and mixture boils and thickens slightly.
Remove saucepan from heat and stir in pineapple and green chilies.
If not serving right away, cover and refrigerate to serve cold later.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of pan.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in 375° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cheese parfait
directions: Beat milk and sugar into cream cheese until smooth.
Mix in topping; layer with strawberries in 6 parfait glasses.
Chill.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine in pan; add flour.
Add milk in small amounts until smooth.
Then add water, salt and cheese.
Reduce heat until cheese melts and sauce begins to thicken.
Pour over 8 ounces of cooked macaroni.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all first 4 ingredients
together. Roll into small balls.
Put on cookie sheet and put toothpicks into each one.
Put in refrigerator.
Mix chocolate chips and cooking wax.
Keep warm while dipping candy balls.
After dipping, put candy on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake icing(great over boxed brownies or cakes)
directions: Mix cocoa and butter.
Simmer gently until melted.
Add remaining ingredients,
except pecans.
Continue to simmer and stir until smooth.	Add
pecans
and
pour mixture immediately over brownies or sheet cake.
Wait for icing to cool completely before cutting.

title: mexican sandwiches
directions: Make white sauce of butter, flour and tomato pulp. Add remainder of the ingredients and heat well.
Serve over toast.

title: mexican chili-bean coleslaw
directions: Whisk dressing ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to mix and coat.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Put 1/2 stick butter and 1 bag marshmallows in pan, stirring, until melted.
Add one box Rice Krispies.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan; top with melted chocolate.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over moderate heat.
Stir until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Cool mixture to room temperature. Bring water, remaining 2 teaspoons salt and oil to a boil.
Add pasta.
Cook at a rapid boil until pasta is done.
Drain pasta. Rinse with water.
Drain again and cool to room temperature.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and debone chicken, saving broth.
Combine Ro-Tel tomatoes, chicken, onions and celery in broth.
Cook spaghetti in this mixture until done.
When done, add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour into greased pans and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Will make three 8 x 8-inch pans.
If freezing, do not place grated cheese on top until you remove from freezer.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, mushroom soup, pimento and cheese while you cook the macaroni.
Drain macaroni well and combine with above ingredients.
Pour mixture in a 9 x 13-inch dish and top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: date filled cookies
directions: Mix well shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and stir.
Drop with teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of date filling on dough and cover with 1/2 teaspoon of dough.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: sweet and sour meatballs(microwave)
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set pineapple aside.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups liquid.

title: yummy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove from broth.
Peel and cut up potatoes; cook in broth.
Cut up chicken and add to potatoes.
Add soups, vegetables, half of cheese and onions.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: baked fish
directions: Marinate fillets in Ziploc bag with oil and dressing for 2 to 6 hours.
Bake at 350° until fish flakes.
Baste with dressing once during baking.

title: chicken poppy seed casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cut into small pieces.
Mix soup, sour cream and chicken.
In separate bowl, mix crushed Ritz crackers, poppy seed and melted butter.
Spread 1/2 of cracker mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour in chicken mix.
Spread the rest of the crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and soda; set aside.
In saucepan, place water, margarine and cocoa; bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients; mix well.
Set aside.
Mix buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Add to chocolate batter.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done; cool and dice.
Add onion, eggs, seasonings, salad dressing and relish.
Mix well and chill.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra into 9 hot jars, filling to 1/2-inch from the top. Place 1 pepper, 1 garlic clove and 1 teaspoon dill seed in each jar. Bring vinegar and next 3 ingredients to a boil over medium-high heat. Pour over okra, filling to half inch from the top. Remove bubbles; wipe jar rims. Cover at once with metal lids and screw on.

title: hurricane oatmeal cake(good to have on hand for "hurricane watches.")
directions: Combine oatmeal and boiling water; set aside.
Beat together eggs, sugars and oil until blended.
Add sifted flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add oatmeal mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Cook on medium heat.
Let come to a full boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until completely mixed.
Add cereal.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: el rancho casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and cook until tender. Add the rest and simmer 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in 8-inch or 9-inch square baking dish (glass), in following order:
Beans mixed with a little taco sauce, sour cream, shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and grated cheese.

title: lentil nut loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in oil until slightly browned.
Mix ingredients except sesame seed and place in a greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle top with seed.
Bake 30 minutes, covered, then 10 minutes, uncovered.
Can be shaped into patties and cooked on griddle instead.

title: braunschweiger dip ball
directions: Mash sausage; add mayonnaise, 1/3 of cream cheese and rest of ingredients.
Pack firmly into a 2 cup bowl (or smaller margarine tubs) lined with plastic wrap.
Chill several hours.
Turn out and frost with remaining softened cream cheese.
Add cream or milk if too firm.

title: braised wild turkey
directions: Wash, drain and pat turkey dry.
Season cavity with salt and pepper.
Stuff with half the salt pork slices, cover turkey with remainder.
Secure pork with toothpicks, if necessary.
Brown in 400° oven about 1 hour.
Remove salt pork and discard.
Combine broth, onion, carrot, parsley, celery, bay leaves and thyme; add to turkey.
Cover tightly and bake in 300° oven for 2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Baste frequently with broth mixture.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Blend flour and shortening.
Add egg, vinegar, water and salt. Mix together until well blended.
Roll out to desired thickness. Yields 4 pie crusts.

title: strawberries and cream torte
directions: Make cake as directed on package.
Partially thaw strawberries.
Drain, reserving 3/4 cup juice.
Combine fruit and Cool Whip.

title: saucy steak skillet
directions: Coat beef with flour; pound it into beef.
Brown beef in oil in a large skillet.
Push beef aside and stir in onion and bell pepper until tender.
Drain.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, lemonade and cranberry juice in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: mama davis' chocolate icing
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Stir in sugar.
Add milk and stir well.
Cook about 2 minutes after mixture comes to a boil on low heat.
Stir often.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and pecans. Stir to cool until it thickens.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Slowly bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add butter and vanilla.
Take off stove.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
Spread on top.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix together like pie crust.
Sprinkle mixture over one-quart peeled, sliced apples that have been placed in an 8 x 8-inch buttered baking pan.
For richer flavor, a little brown sugar may be added to apples before topping is sprinkled.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Turn upside down and serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
Makes 9 servings.
Double ingredients for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Beat eggs in saucepan.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Heat and beat constantly until thick and smooth.
Add butter and cool.
When cold, add whipped cream, drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Can add nuts.

title: creamy french dressing
directions: Mix and beat with mixer.
Beat hard until creamy thick.
I like to add a little garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: my grandmother's butter cookies
directions: Put raisins in hot water to plump and drain thoroughly. Mix ingredients in order given. Spray cookie sheet with Pam or leave ungreased. Drop cookies by rounded teaspoonful. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Let set a little before removing from cookie sheet. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: raspberry salad jello mold
directions: Prepare jello as directed on package.
Add applesauce and raspberries.
Mold and refrigerate.

title: maryland cream of crab soup
directions: Remove cartilage from crab meat.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
In 4-quart saucepan, cook onion in margarine or butter until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk and bouillon gradually and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens enough to coat spoon.
Add crab meat; heat, but do not boil.
Garnish with parsley flakes before serving. Makes 6 servings.
Soup improves upon standing as flavors get a chance to blend, so this a good "prepare ahead" dish.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread soft cream cheese on shallow 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with salsa.
Add peppers, onions, and tomatoes on top.
Add cheese last.
Chill in fridge and serve.

title: lentil roast
directions: Mince onion and brown in part of oil.
Add lentils and other ingredients.
Bake in oiled loaf pan at 375° for 1 hour.

title: marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add meat or seafood and cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Marinade can be reused.

title: truffles
directions: Over low heat, melt chocolate chips and condensed milk, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Chill 2 hours and shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll in any of the suggested coatings and chill 1 hour.
Store in covered container at room temperature.

title: steak bake
directions: Brown steak in skillet and layer in large baking dish.
Saut pepper and onion rings in same skillet until just limp and layer over steak.
Pour spaghetti sauce over steak and vegetables.
Cover with tin foil.
Bake about 45 minutes on 350 degrees.
Remove from oven.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle cheeses over top and return to oven until it melts.
Serve over noodles or spaghetti.

title: yam pie
directions: Add sugar and butter to mashed yams.
Add well beaten eggs and beat until smooth.
Add milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook in 350° oven until done.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.

title: banana pudding
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, combine sugar, flour, salt, milk, egg yolks and butter; mix well.
Cook on High until mixture thickens, stirring frequently.
Add vanilla and stir well.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and put in long casserole dish.
Top with corn flake crumbs mixed with 3/4 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and cocoa.
Add salad dressing, water or coffee and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured cake pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: grilled halibut
directions: In a large dish or Ziploc bag, put lemon juice and rind, garlic and salt.
Add fish; turn to coat.
Leave in at least 30 minutes.
Spread mayonnaise thinly over fish; grill until fish flakes, turning once.
Serve with sauce.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Bake
30 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Serve with warm milk. You can mix it the night before; refrigerate and bake the next day. Serves 9.

title: shrimp-chicken jambalaya
directions: Coat a large skillet with vegetable cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper; saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is done, stirring occasionally.

title: linda's beef stew
directions: Place flour in plastic bag.
Add meat cubes, a few at a time, shaking to coat.
In a large skillet brown meat, half at a time, in hot oil.
Layer in Crock Pot, potatoes, onion, carrots and celery.
Put meat on top of vegetables, pour V-8 juice over the meat. Cover, cook on low setting for 10-12 hours or till meat and vegetables are tender.
Serve with buttered bread!

title: two hour buns
directions: Mix water, sugar, oil and eggs together; set aside.
In another bowl mix 2 tablespoons yeast in 4 cups flour.
Add to water, sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix together.
Mix salt into 2 more cups flour and add to first mixture and mix together.
Add rest of flour to make soft dough.
Let raise 15 minutes.
Knead; let raise 15 minutes more.
Put in pans and let raise 1 hour or until double.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 48 small buns or 24 large buns.

title: raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients; add margarine, orange peel, eggs and nonfat milk.
Mix until blended.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Place in well-greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until loaf tests done. Remove from pan and store 12 hours before slicing.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine spinach with cottage cheese and eggs.
Mix well.
Add salt and Parmesan.
Continue to mix until blended.
Pour into a greased shallow casserole or 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Make into balls about the size of a quarter.
Freeze after rolling into balls.
Defrost before baking.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in oven at 350°.
Makes 40 to 50 balls.

title: fish and chips
directions: Cut fillets into pieces, about 3 x 1 1/2-inches.
Place on paper towels to dry.
Beat egg yolks until thick and light. Blend in beer, milk, flour and seasonings.
Mix until smooth. Beat egg whites stiff but not dry; fold in.
Pat fillets dry.
Dip into batter, a few pieces at a time; lift out and drain slightly with fork or slotted spoon.
Fry in deep fat heated to 375° for 2 to 3 minutes until golden brown and puffed.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve with French fried potatoes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil noodles in salt until tender; drain and rinse in cold water.
Cook hamburger until gray; drain grease.
Add Chili-O chili powder, oregano and tomato sauce.
In a dish, layer the noodles, sauce mixture, noodles, sauce mixture and Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck and Italian sausage.
Saute onion, green pepper, mushrooms and garlic with meat the last 10 minutes.
Drain meat and then add Italian pear tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Layer in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish:

1/2 sauce, 1/2 zucchini, cottage or Ricotta cheese, 1/2 mixture of Mozzarella/Cheddar/Provolone cheese, 1/2 Parmesan cheese, remainder of zucchini, remainder of sauce, remainder of cheese mixture and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Allow to cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut and serve.
Makes about 8 adult servings.

title: pudding - cool dessert
directions: Crush crackers.
Mix with butter and press in 9 x 13-inch pan (save some for top if desired).

title: sunny carrot salad(fat-free)
directions: Mix all ingredients in serving bowl.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until yolks and whites are blended.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk slowly.
Pour into a pastry lined pie shell.
Bake at 425° until you can insert knife and it comes out clean.

title: booze cake
directions: Cover raisins with water and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Drain, saving 3/4 cup cooking liquid.
Cool.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Beat in egg.
Sift together flour, soda, spices and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture alternately with cooking liquid.
Stir in raisins, nuts and whiskey.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool thoroughly.
Frost tops and sides with Bourbon Hard Sauce.
Decorate top with walnut halves.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, milk and Old Bay, then add crab meat; work through.
Form ball and place in center of plate.
Pour cocktail sauce over ball and serve with crackers.

title: tortilla roll away
directions: Mix the top 5 ingredients; spread evenly on tortillas.
Roll tightly.
Wrap in wax paper and place in refrigerator to chill at least 3 hours.
Remove from refrigerator; cut each roll into 1-inch pieces.
Stick toothpick in each piece.
Makes 70 to 80 pieces.

title: easy green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Spoon into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Combine sauce mix, tomato sauce and water and simmer.
Brown meat, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper and pour into sauce. Simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Cook spaghetti; drain. Wash in hot water.
Pour sauce over spaghetti to serve.

title: thin vanilla icing
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Ice the Danish Puff while still warm. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and cherries, if you wish.
Cut into squares for serving.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil the chicken, then chip into small pieces.
Place stick of butter in a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish and melt in oven.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together and set aside.

title: pistachio angels
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line 2 cookie sheets with foil; set aside.

title: plain cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Alternately add flour, eggs, milk and vanilla flavoring.

title: festive cranberry salad
directions: In a bowl, combine milk and lemon juice; mix well. Stir in pineapple, pecans, cranberry sauce and mini marshmallows. Add food coloring, if desired. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight. Cut in squares. Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs.
Stir in nuts and strawberries.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put all ingredients (except peanuts and baking soda) into saucepan.
Let sugar start to melt and then add peanuts.
Cook until peanuts taste roasted.
(You can test this by cooling a peanut in a glass of cold water and then tasting.)
Add baking soda and pour into 2 buttered pizza pans.
Break when cooled.

title: vegetarian pasta primavera
directions: Steam broccoli and asparagus for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in oil in a large pan until tender.
Add carrots and chopped peppers to onion mixture and saute until crisp-tender.
Remove from heat and drain.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and press the slivered almonds into the butter.
Mash the banana and beat with the eggs and rum.
Add pound cake mix and beat until smooth.
Stir in sour cream and nutmeg.
Pour carefully into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 to 75 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake
at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf or 12 muffins.
Mix preceding ingredients
and fold into loaf pan or muffin pan.

title: cherry delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix graham crackers and oleo. Spread in pie pan.

title: coconut fruit dip
directions: Mix sour cream with brown sugar.
Break cookies into small chunks and stir into sour cream mixture just until moist. Refrigerate overnight.
(Can be served with most any fruit you enjoy.)

title: old-fashion vinegar pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar.
Add eggs and vinegar.
Add water and extract.
Add butter just before your take from heat.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: family casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onions, stirring to separate meat. Stir in soup, water, peas and macaroni.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 375° oven about 25 minutes until bubbly hot.

title: chocolate syrup for ice cream
directions: In large saucepan, mix sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add hot water and whisk until smooth.
Over medium heat, bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and stir.
Pour into jar and let cool. Cover and refrigerate.
Can be heated in microwave to warm before serving, if desired.
Makes 2 cups.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, onions, green and red peppers and salt; let stand overnight.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain well.
Add vinegar, sugar, celery seed, nutmeg, turmeric, mustard and cornstarch; mix well.
Cook for 30 minutes; place in clean, hot jars.
Seal.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes to complete seal.
Yield:
About 6 pints.

title: beef chicken burritos
directions: Brown hamburger and onion with 1/2 packet of taco seasoning. Put 3 tablespoons of meat mixture in soft tortilla.
Sprinkle with cheese and roll-up.
Put in baking dish.
Heat soup up with 1 can of milk.
Pour over burritos.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients well and put in a baking dish.

title: butterscotch spectacular
directions: For crust:
Mix flour, margarine (melted) and chopped pecans together and press in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown, then cool.

title: frozen jello punch
directions: Combine gelatin and sugar in large bowl.
Add one quart boiling water; mix well.
Add one quart cold water along with the lemon juice and pineapple juice; mix well.
Pour into one-gallon container and freeze.
Freeze until firm.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, milk chocolate chips and butter.
Pour over cereal and mix well.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over mixture and mix well again.
Store in an airtight container.

title: raw apple cake and frosting
directions: Mix together with a spoon; do not use a mixer.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cajun pot roast
directions: Cut holes (or pockets) in roast and stuff with garlic, green onions and green peppers.
Sprinkle roast with cayenne pepper and salt.
Put roast in roasting bag that has been floured with 2 tablespoons flour.
Place in shallow pan.
Put mushrooms, potatoes, carrots, parsley and chopped green onions on and around roast.
Cover roast and vegetables with mixture of water, wine, soy sauce and celery.
Punch holes in roasting bag (top) and tie bag.
Cook at 325° to 350° until done, 3 to 4 hours, depending on size of roast.

title: monkey bread
