directions: Shake the biscuits in a paper bag with 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Layer half of the biscuits in a well-greased Bundt pan.
Melt the margarine, 3/4 cup of brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour half of this mixture over the biscuits and sprinkle with half the nuts.
Repeat with the remaining biscuits, sauce and nuts.
Bake at 350° about 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes, then turn out and enjoy.

title: creamy lettuce toss
directions: Mix mayonnaise with sour cream.
Toss with remaining ingredients.

title: sausage bread
directions: Crumble and fry sausage.
Saute onion.
Mix ingredients.
Bake in a greased 8 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple salad with 7-up
directions: Mix Jell-O in hot water and 7-Up and let start to set.
Add drained pineapple to Jell-O.
Cook pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Fold pudding into whipped cream and spread on top of Jell-O.

title: chicken italian
directions: Dip chicken breasts into melted butter and place skin side up onto a cookie tray.
Thoroughly coat the chicken with the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: shrimp sour dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend until smooth.

title: lobster or crab supreme
directions: Cut lettuce in half; make a firm cup by taking out some of the center.
Cut off both ends of a tomato, take out the core, cut into eighths, but do not cut all the way through.
Marinate the sea legs in lemon juice, white pepper, mayonnaise and chopped celery.
Use ice cream scoop; fill center of tomato.
Put the tomato into the lettuce cup and gently open the tomato.
Garnish with olives or sliced cucumbers.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add cooled pinto beans.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Get oven hot then turn down to 275° and bake for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: winter stew delight
directions: Preheat oven. Combine all ingredients in large pot. Cover and bake, stirring occasionally. If necessary, add more broth or tomato juice.

title: white chocolate pretzels
directions: Melt chocolate according to package instructions in a large bowl.
Drop pretzels into melted chocolate (about 2 handfuls at a time) and stir until pretzels are fully covered.
Place on wax paper or aluminum foil and allow to set.
Drop another 2 handfuls and do the same as above.
Continue until you've used all of the chocolate.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: In one-quart shallow casserole dish, combine peaches, sugar, 1 tablespoon of baking mix and cinnamon.
In separate bowl, mix 2/3 cup of baking mix with brown sugar.
Cut in margarine.
Stir in milk until moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto peaches.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix first 3 ingredients in a saucepan using medium to high heat.
Just don't scorch.
Bring to the bubbling point.
Stir gently to dissolve sugar.
Do not boil! Cook 4 minutes.
A low heat will do for this.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat fudge, just a few minutes. When thick enough, pour into pan.
Allow to cool and cut into squares.

title: meat on a stick
directions: Combine red pepper, garlic powder and seasoned salt in a wide, shallow bowl.
Add beef and mix with hands to coat with spices. Preheat broiler.
Thread beef and onion pieces onto 12-inch skewers.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes per side or until meat is tender. Makes 8 skewers.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Prepare oven to 350°.
Mix soup, rice and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Cheez Whiz and put in oven to melt cheese.

title: buttermilk oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix oatmeal and buttermilk; let stand 10 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add the oatmeal mixture.
In a small bowl, mix flour, leavening and salt.
Add to the moist mixture.
Add the nuts and dates; blend gently until just mixed.
Put in lined or greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together with only 1/2 cup nuts.
Form into a ball and refrigerate.
When chilled, roll ball in remaining nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: cranberry strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into mold or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Serve with dressing made of Miracle Whip, sugar and cream.

title: corn casserole
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish and top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° until hot and bubbly, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: linda's lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
On low heat cook next 6 ingredients. Cool lasagna noodles as directed on package.
Grease (or use Pam) large casserole dish.

title: texas sombreros
directions: Melt butter in skillet, saute celery, onion, green pepper and cook until tender.
Add meat, salt, pepper, steak sauce and chili powder.
Brown.
Add canned tomatoes, tomato sauce and sugar. Simmer 30 minutes until thick.
Serve over corn chips, topped with cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: barbara's overnight buns
directions: In separate bowl, mix together 3 3/4 cups flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Scald milk and sugar, then cool.
Add yeast in milk (set for 5 minutes).
Then add beaten egg, melted shortening and 4 cups flour.
Cover.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Then add the 3 3/4 cups flour mixture.
Place mixture in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Lightly grease top of each bun.

title: sweet meatballs
directions: Mix in medium bowl the beef, onions, egg, oatmeal, crackers, garlic powder and salt and pepper like meat loaf.
Roll into 1-inch balls and bake in oven at 350° until brown and done.
Then in saucepan, mix ketchup, jelly and barbecue sauce and simmer over medium heat until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs to sauce and enjoy.

title: homemade chow-chow relish
directions: Grind cabbage, onions, green tomatoes, hot peppers and bell peppers in food grinder.
Add water and salt and let set overnight.
Squeeze out juice and rinse in cold water.
Add pickling spice, sugar, mustard seed and vinegar.
Cook until brown.
Keep canning jars and lids in hot water until ready to fill with Chow-Chow.
Put lids on tight.

title: rhubarb-strawberry jam
directions: Mix sugar and rhubarb and let stand overnight in glass or pottery bowl.
Boil for 15 minutes. Add berries during last 5 minutes.
Pour in pineapple and juice.
Cook a few minutes.
Add gelatin and mix well.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles.
Add sugar and butter.
Put half into two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Mix other ingredients together; put 1/2 into each 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cherries on top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: strawberry and pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and spread over pretzel mix.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs in half lengthwise.
Slip out yolks and mash with fork.
Mix in seasonings and salad dressing.
Fill white part of egg halves with yolk mixture, heaping it up high.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes in three 8 1/2 x 4 1/3 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.

title: lye soap(this is just a sample of what we use to do in the old days.)
directions: This should be done in a well ventilated area, preferably outside, using a large cast-iron pot.
If you use your own grease, skim off only the top and add Borax.
Mix water and grease; bring this mixture to a boil.
Pour lye into boiled ingredients being very careful with lye.
Bring to second boil.
Add 3 gallons water.
Cook until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Boil mixture 3 hours.
Can leave in pot or pour into wooden or cardboard box lined with freezer paper with wax side up.
Do not use aluminum. Let soap set for 24 hours, then cut into squares.
Wrap in wax paper and store for 5 weeks or 6 months.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Stir in cheese cubes last.
Bake at 350°, covered, for one hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Split into small pieces.
Put in bottom of baking pan.
Mix soup and sour cream together; spread on top of chicken.
Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Pour on top of soup mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sachertorte
directions: Melt chocolate in top of a double boiler.
Add butter, stirring until melted.
Add egg yolks, beating constantly.
Add sugar and beat until well mixed.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in chocolate mixture and flour alternately.
Pour into a greased 8 inch square pan lined with greased waxed paper. Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Melt jam in hot water.
Spread on top of cake.
Let stand 20 minutes and then decorate with frosting.

title: icy holiday punch
directions: In a 4-quart freezerproof container, dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water. Stir in pineapple juice and cold water. Cover and freeze overnight. Remove from freezer 2 hours before stirring. Place in punch bowl; stir in ginger ale just before serving. Makes 32 to 36 servings.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add onions, peppers and sauce to ground beef.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: lemon tonic
directions: Dissolve sugar in lemon juice.
Add cloves.
Pour in tonic water.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with lemon slice.

title: dirt cups
directions: Crush cookies, pour milk into pail. Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened. Stir in whipped topping. Gradually stir in 1 cup of the crushed cookies. Top with remaining cookies. Refrigerate until ready to use. Decorate with candy and serve.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, then hot broth; cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup sauce, chicken, 1 cup cheese, chiles and cumin; mix well.
Dip each tortilla into remaining sauce to soften; fill each with chicken mixture.
Roll up.
Arrange in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over them. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 25 minutes.
Garnish as desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pride of iowa cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Beat in eggs.
Add vanilla. Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to sugar, shortening and egg mixture.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Either drop from spoon on cookie sheet, flattening the cookies with bottom of glass dipped into flour, or form dough into rolls, chill and slice.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: golden puffs(donut holes)
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg or mace.
Add oil, milk and egg.
Stir with a fork until thoroughly mixed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls (to large of puffs will not cook through) into deep hot oil at 375°.
Fry until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper.

title: red cherry salad
directions: Add sugar to cherries; bring to boil.
Add cherry Jell-O. Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water; add to first mixture.
Add pineapple (do not drain), orange juice, orange rind and nuts. Mold.

title: jail house biscuits
directions: Stir the yeast into the 1 1/2 cups warm water.
Mix oleo, sugar, salt and potatoes.
Add flour, then water with yeast as needed; mix well.
Place in greased bowl; cover with damp cloth. Place in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out biscuits as needed. Let rise.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: apple rings
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Put syrup ingredients in 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Place pan in oven, stirring occasionally until sugars dissolve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach
on
paper
towel
until moisture is out. Mix all ingredients and let set overnight.

title: stir-fry nappa (chinese cabbage) with sweet-sour sauce
directions: Heat frying pan and saute nappa, ginger and hot peppers with cooking oil.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Nappa is very tender.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix well.
Keep refrigerated until using.
Very good, especially with home baked bread.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Cook pork chops.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup of cheese and 1/2 can onion rings.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chops over potatoes.
Bake, covered, for 40 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in greased muffin tins or can bake in round pans. Bake in a 400° oven for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: braised, stuffed flank steak
directions: Combine crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, pepper, celery salt and sage.
Arrange in pocket of steak.
Dot with butter.
Close as tightly as possible and secure with skewers (or toothpicks).

title: rigatoni, broccoli and mozzarella melt
directions: Make a sauce, melting butter in a heavy, medium saucepan.
Add garlic and cook until softened.
Stir in flour.
Cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Stir in milk and salt.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Cook broccoli florets 2 minutes in boiling water, drain and rinse.
Return to pan.
Toss with 1 tablespoon olive oil and set aside.
Toss cooked rigatoni with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Place 3/4 cup sauce into oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Put 1/2 of the rigatoni over sauce and scatter 1/2 of the broccoli on top.
Drizzle 3/4 cup sauce over all and repeat with remaining rigatoni, broccoli and sauce.
Sprinkle evenly with shredded cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: apple date-nut bread
directions: Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans and flour.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Shape into balls the size of small walnuts.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: strawberry spread(diabetic)
directions: Combine strawberries, 1/2 cup water, lemon juice and cinnamon in a small Dutch oven, stirring well; bring mixture to a boil.

title: party candies
directions: Stir together butter, corn syrup, salt, vanilla and desired extract.
Gradually add powdered sugar and stir until the mixture is smooth.
Knead in the last of the powdered sugar with your hands.
Add desired food coloring.
Knead until the food coloring is evenly distributed.
Roll candy into balls; coat with granulated sugar and press into molds.
Remove from molds.
Cover candies with paper towels; let dry overnight.
Store in a tightly covered container.
Makes 96 candies.

title: cool corn casserole
directions: Combine all vegetables and moisten with mayonnaise.
Crumble Fritos and pour on top before serving.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook and stir mushrooms and green pepper in margarine over medium heat 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in bouillon, milk, water and mushrooms.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly for 1 minute. Stir in turkey and pimiento.
Serves 6.

title: scramble party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a very large pan or 7-quart canner then pour into a large baking pan (can use large turkey baking pan). Bake in 250° oven for 2 hours.
Be sure to stir every 15 minutes. Can freeze mix.
Plastic Cool-Whip containers are good to use.

title: french butter cream cookies
directions: Mix together and chill 30 minutes.
Shape into small balls and flatten with a fork that has been dipped in water.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 48.

title: overnight refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water, add oil, sugar, eggs and 4 cups flour and salt.
Mix well until smooth.
Add rest of flour.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Bake at 350° until browned. Makes about 36 rolls.
Not necessary to knead this dough.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into pan and sprinkle Ritz cracker crumbs on top.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.
Great for diabetics.

title: heavenly apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Stir in cold water and chill until partially set.
Add pineapple, apples and nuts to jello mixture; chill until firm. Beat sugar, lemon juice and eggs together.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over jello; chill.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Use oblong baking dish for doubling recipe or square dish for single quantity.
Partly drain tomatoes.
Layer tomatoes, stuffing mix, onions, etc.
Top with grated sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Thaw the vegetables under cold water and drain well.
Drain the chicken and combine all the ingredients in a casserole dish except 1/4 of the onions.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and add onions.
Separate 1 (5 count) package of flaky refrigerator biscuits.
Divide each into thin rounds.
Place on top of the hot chicken mixture and bake, uncovered, 10 additional minutes until biscuits are brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add green beans, garlic, cumin, water and tomato sauce.
Blend in 6 jalapeno peppers.
Pour in skillet. Bring to boil about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water until fork easily pierces potatoes.
Cool slightly.
Remove skins.
Place cooked and peeled potatoes in large mixing bowl.
Mix with mixer until smooth.
There should be about 3 1/2 cups mashed potatoes.
Stir in butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in nutmeg, salt and Pet milk.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 minutes.
Lower heat to 325°.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes longer or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: reuben soup
directions: Cook bacon, do not drain.
Add melted butter, celery and onions and saute for 2 minutes.
Add flour until well blended, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add water, chicken and ham base, sauerkraut, corned beef and caraway seeds.
Heat and gently boil for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add cheese and heat to simmering for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: easy fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake golden butter cake according to directions. Let cool completely and split layers to make 4 layers instead of 2. While cake is baking, pour sour cream, sugar and 2 packages of frozen coconut into bowl. Stir mixture every now and then. Thaw remaining package of frozen coconut, reserving this for the top and sides. Frost and stack layers with the coconut, sour cream and sugar mixture. Cover the top and sides with dessert topping and sprinkle coconut on top and sides.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, soup and chicken broth. Top with margarine and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheeseburger skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion with oregano until tender; stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: boots' baked beans
directions: Mix well. Place bacon deep in beans. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Put all ingredients in a buttered pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: grandma's apple butter
directions: Will also need pint jars.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together the flour, soda, cinnamon and sugar.
To this mixture, add eggs and beat well.
Add 2 cups of pumpkin and beat again.
Add oil and beat again.
Bake in layer pans or oblong pan at 350° until done.

title: pumpkin raisin muffins
directions: Stir all dry
ingredients
together.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake in sprayed (Pam) muffin tins at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef sukiyaki
directions: Brown beef strips in oil.
Sprinkle garlic powder and 1/8 teaspoon of ginger and brown together.
Add 1/4 cup of soy sauce. Add cauliflower and pepper to meat.
Cover and let simmer.
Mix can of beef broth and cornstarch and add this to the meat mixture. Add mushrooms and sugar to ingredients.
Heat until thickens. Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix together, by hand, powdered sugar, graham crumbs and peanut butter in bowl.
Add enough melted margarine to mix thoroughly.
(Amount of melted margarine needed depends on oils in various peanut butters.)
Press into 9 x 14-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: chopped broccoli soup
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients
all together until tender.
Add 1/3 cup flour; stir.
Add the Pet milk.
Be sure and do not boil. Add the chicken broth.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: sweet roll dough(richer dough)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in remaining ingredients, using 1/2 flour.
Mix until smooth. Add remaining flour.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Round up in greased bowl.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours until doubled.
Punch down.
Let rise again until almost doubled (30 minutes). Divide dough for rolls or coffee cakes.
Let rise until light.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable cole slaw
directions: Grate vegetables.
Boil vinegar, sugar and water.
Add seasoning to it.
Pour over vegetables. Can be kept in refrigerator.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Mix and let sit overnight.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Roll roast in flour'n brown in heated salad oil in large pot. Stir in broth, peppercorns, salt and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil...reduce to low heat'n simmer kivered fur about 2 hours.
Now add taters, celery, carrots and onions.
Put in more watah 'r broth if needed to kiver vegetables 'n cook one more hor or til meat 'n taters are tender.
Put meat 'n vegetables on hot platter 'n sprinkle with parsley.
Pore off fat'n thicken gravy remainin'.

title: bitsy bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 3 pieces; roll into small ball.
Roll in honey and coconut.
Place 3 balls in a muffin cup pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 people.

title: emmy's cookies(a sugar cookie)
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg substitute.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with yogurt.
Drop on cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 12 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Melt cranberry sauce over medium heat.
Drain, reserving liquid and berries.
Mix together cranberry liquid, boiling water and Jell-O; stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Chill until mixture mounds slightly on a spoon.
Add mayonnaise and beat until smooth.
Fold in cranberries, apples and nuts.
Pour into a 2-quart bowl.
Chill overnight.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken parts.
Put in heated oven at 350°. Let brown on both sides.
Combine ingredients and pour over chicken.
Let bake for about 1 hour.
Turn over as needed.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan; line bottom with wax paper. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix canning salt with sliced cucumbers, cover with ice and let stand 3 hours. Mix sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed, bring to a boil. Drain cucumbers well; add onions and peppers to vinegar mixture. Heat to boiling. Fill jars and seal.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream sugars and egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add milk and vanilla with any ingredients.
Spread evenly in 11 x 16-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let set and make topping.

title: topsy turvy cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt in a small bowl, beating until well blended.
Stir in chips.
Mix flour with 1 cup sugar, cocoa, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a large mixer bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Fill 18 paper baking cups, set in muffin pans, half full with batter.
Top each with 1 tablespoon cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: joan's scotch shortbread
directions: With mixer, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add 2 cups flour, a little at a time.
When flour is all blended, add another 1/4 cup flour by hand.
Press firmly into 7 1/2 x 12-inch pan and prick top with fork to make dots in a row.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased bread pan.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Put just one cup flour in this batch.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Mix on medium speed.
Mix in egg yolks.
Dissolve soda in water.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add spices, flavoring and remaining 2 cups of flour.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter. Fold in fruit mixture.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Stir in egg.
Mix soda into applesauce and stir into sugar mixture alternately with flour and spices.
Stir in raisins.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or less. Check for doneness with toothpick.

title: blarney stone bread
directions: Combine ingredients; blend.
Cut 1 loaf of French bread in half lengthwise.
Spread mixture on two cut sides.
Broil until lightly browned and bubbly.
Cut into diagonal slices.

title: meat loaf roll
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for cheese.
On waxed paper or foil, pat meat to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle cheese on top of meat, leaving a small margin around edges.
Starting from one end, carefully roll up meat, using paper to lift.
Seal edges and ends.
Place roll, seam side down, in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour 3/4 cup each of Ragu sauce and barbecue sauce over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° until done, 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Line a pie plate with the crescent rolls; set aside.
Brown the hamburger with the onion until both are thoroughly cooked; drain off fat.
Add tomato paste and Italian seasoning to meat and onion.
Mix well and heat.
Place meat in pie plate; top with cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until crescent roll crust and cheese are browned.

title: shrimp and pasta salad(4 servings)
directions: Whisk together olive oil, vinegar, thyme, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add shrimp, pasta, green peas and tomatoes to dressing.
Cover and let stand 1 hour, tossing occasionally. Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: eggnog
directions: With a mixer, beat eggs alone until well blended.
Add sugar and salt and mix well until thick and fluffy.
Stir milk by hand. Chill.

title: topsy turvey sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Beat egg and add milk.
Add. Add flour, baking powder, vanilla and lemon.
Roll out and bake at 350° for 13 minutes.
(Ovens vary.)
Rolls out best if chilled for 2 hours.

title: potted beef brisket
directions: Brown brisket; keep turning and brown until it has all been seared.
If it sticks as you brown, add water, a little at a time. When good and brown, slice the onions and garlic; continue to brown.
Still add water if it sticks.
When all brown, take a cup of water (not full).
Shake in about 1/4 cup of ketchup.
Shake in Worcestershire sauce into cup, also salt.
Cook for 1 hour.
Take meat out and slice thin.
Put back in pot and keep cooking for about 2 1/2 hours more.
The last 1/2 hour, put in the mushrooms and cut up potatoes.
"It's outrageous."

title: fantasy ambrosia
directions: Toss bananas with orange juice; drain, reserving juice.
Layer oranges, bananas and strawberries in serving bowl.
Chill.
Combine salad dressing, orange juice and sugar.
Fold in whipped cream. Spoon over fruit.
Garnish with coconut.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.

title: angel dip
directions: Mix together Eagle brand milk and lemon juice; add coconut, pecans, drained pineapple and cool whip. Chill in refrigerator overnight. Good as a salad or dessert. (Serve with cookie.)

title: dinner plate tacos
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet.
Drain fat.
Add taco seasoning mix and follow directions on package.
Dice tomatoes, finely chop lettuce and shred Cheddar cheese.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Place in a casserole dish. Place pork chops over potatoes.
Pour mushroom soup over this. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put cheese on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red sherbet smash
directions: In punch bowl, combine red punch drink mix, lemonade concentrate and water.
Stir to dissolve.
Chill.
Before serving, pour in lemonade-lime beverage.
Float small scoops of sherbet on top.
Garnish with lemon slices, if desired.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: sesame chicken kabobs
directions: *Example:
red and yellow peppers, mushrooms, zucchini and onion, etc.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar.
Stand 15 minutes.
Sift flour before measuring.
Add baking powder and salt.
Add lard to bananas.
Mix and beat.
Add dry ingredients, soda, beaten eggs and nuts.
Stir only until well mixed.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: thirty day salad
directions: Bring last five ingredients to boil.
Cool and pour over chopped vegetables.
Good as salad or on hot dogs.

title: candy cookies
directions: Boil for 2 minutes in a large pan the granulated sugar, cocoa powder, margarine and milk; stir as it cooks.
Remove from heat and mix in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Spoon out on wax paper. One or two spoonfuls makes a cookie. Let cool before you remove cookies from wax paper.

title: beans by george
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and combine with beans in roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Freezes well!

title: almond flavored chocolate cherry cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients until well blended. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake according to mix directions. Let cool and frost with chocolate frosting.

title: butter cookies (rolled)
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Cut in the butter as for pie crust.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla. Add them to the flour mixture.
Blend well.
Let dough stand a short time before rolling out.
Sugar may be sprinkled over the top, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on hot dog buns and wrap individually in foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: beef marinade
directions: Marinate the meat at least 24 hours.
Turn meat a couple of times.

title: speedy raisin sauce for ham
directions: In medium saucepan, blend together brown sugar, dry mustard, and ginger.
Stir in raisin pie filling, 2 tablespoons water, the vinegar, and Worcestershire sauce; heat to boiling.
Serve with ham.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: skillet macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain noodles.
Slightly saute onion in the 1/4 cup butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.
Good with any kind of cheese.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon and drain.
Add onion and cook slightly.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans, and bring to a boil.
Add all the beans.
Mix well and put in casserole or crockpot.
Garnish with strips of bacon.
Bake 40 minutes at 350 degrees.
In crock pot, on high for 1 to 2 hours, then turn down to low.
Stir occasionally.

title: watermelon pie
directions: For watermelon juice:
Cut watermelon into cubes and push through strainer.
One quarter of large watermelon will yield 2 1/2 cups juice.

title: boiled egg pie
directions: Peel eggs.
Cut 6 eggs	in thirds and lay in pan;
salt and pepper.
Cover with
water	and
put
oleo in water; cover with a layer of dumplings.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit together; add sliced bananas.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over fruit and mix.
Chill and serve.

title: frosted mocha brownies
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Blend melted chocolate with coffee; set aside to cool.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream butter with vanilla extract until butter is softened.
Add sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy, after each addition.
Add beaten eggs in thirds, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Blend in cooled chocolate, beating only until smooth after each addition.
Add dry ingredients in thirds. Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: smoked turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let salad set at least an hour, longer if can, to blend flavors!
Yum.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Boil pineapple 2 minutes.
Pour
jello	in cup with 1/2 package plain gelatin.
Finish
filling
cup
with cold water. Pour this in hot pineapple	juice.	Boil additional 2 minutes. Cool and then fold in 8
ounces
cottage
cheese
and 8 ounces Cool Whip.	Put in refrigerator to congeal.

title: walnut sandwich
directions: Spread bread with salad dressing.
Chop up nuts and fill sandwich and enjoy.

title: cheesy beans and brown rice
directions: Cook rice.
Cook onion, carrot, celery, basil, oregano and garlic in oil until tender.
Add beans and tomato; heat through. Add cheese and butter to rice.
Add vegetable mixture.
Serve immediately.
Serves 5.

title: popcorn crunch
directions: Cook syrup and sugar to hard ball stage in doubler boiler. Pour over popped corn in a buttered dish.
Add pecans and almonds.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Dissolve jello and water in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Mix together.
Let it get firm in refrigerator. Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Measure dry ingredients. Sift together. Add remaining ingredients. Stir the mixture to blend (do not beat). Pour into a greased 9-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for about an hour. Set aside to cool on rack without removing from pan.

title: tops and bottoms
directions: Wash greens; drain and chop into medium pieces.
Peel turnips and quarter.
Rinse salt pork; pat dry.
Slice into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Cook pork slices in 8-quart Dutch oven until golden brown.
Slowly pour in water and bring to a boil.
Cook pork on low about 20 minutes or until tender.
Add chopped turnip greens, onion and sugar.
Cook slowly about 15 minutes.
Add turnips and cook 15 minutes more or until all is tender.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate for several hours.
Roll thick (1/2-inch) on floured board.
Cut and bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Frost when cooled.

title: shrimp with angel hair pasta
directions: Saute mushrooms and scallions until tender.
In another pot, cook wine, tomato paste, tarragon, salt, pepper and eggs.
Cook down to 1/2 cup of liquid and sauce consistency.
Put in mushrooms and scallions.
Pour over hot pasta and sprinkle with cooked shrimp.

title: plantation creams
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar.
Mix baking soda and salt with sour cream.
Immediately add to butter, sugar mixture. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add flour, blending thoroughly.
Drop by the spoonful on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Garnish with nuts, if desired.

title: vanilla almond coffee
directions: Pour coffee into a large, self-closing plastic bag or large bowl.
Add both extracts to coffee.
Thoroughly blend extracts into coffee.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator or freezer until ready to use.
Brew coffee as usual.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Mix in a bowl rice and soup (do not add water).
Spread in the pan and place chicken on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 375°.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put in greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: dixie's retirement punch
directions: Mix well and freeze.
Remove from freezer 3 to 5 hours before serving.
Serve slushy.

title: peppery pear relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle, mixing well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour hot mixture into hot, sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles; wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw on bands.
Process relish in boiling water bath for 20 minutes.
Yields 12 pints.

title: raspberry oatmeal bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine dry cake mix and oats in large bowl.
Add melted butter and stir until crumbly.
Measure 3 cups of mixture into pan.
Press firmly to cover bottom of pan.
Combine preserves and water, spread over mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs, pat firmly to make top. Bake for 18 to 23 minutes or until top is golden.
Cool completely on rack.
Cut into bars.
Store in airtight container.

title: hot dog meat sauce
directions: Brown onion slightly in margarine. Add ground beef and brown, breaking with fork as it browns. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour.
If too thin, cook, uncovered, until it thickens a little more.
Serve over hot dogs in roll.
Makes 12 servings.
Serving size:
1 serving.
Preparation time:
1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Dice 3 bananas on top of crust. Place 1/2 inch slices of Neopolitan ice cream (slightly softened) on top of bananas. Sprinkle with nuts and freeze.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: s'more bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt syrup, butter and chips until it reaches boiling.
Pour over cereal and marshmallows.
Stir and pat in pan.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: taco dip(alpo dip)
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain. Add taco seasoning.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Heat in small crock-pot or saucepan until hot, but do not boil.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sizzle chicken party snackshouston, texas
directions: Cut each chicken breast halve lengthwise into 4 long strips (16 total).
In a large nonmetal bowl, combine soy sauce, sherry, basil, garlic, honey, ginger root, pepper, crushed red pepper and five-spice powder.
Add chicken strips and stir to coat. Cover and marinate for at least 30 minutes at room temperature or 4 to 24 hours in the refrigerator.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook all until peanuts pop; take off heat, then add soda.
Pour out onto greased cookie sheet. Let set and cool.

title: green rice bake
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 35 to 40 minutes, or until firm.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Heat butter in heavy skillet and saute the onion, garlic and cucumbers in it until onion is tender, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with the flour; stir well.
Gradually stir in the broth.
Add the salt and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until cucumbers are tender.
Cool.
Puree the mixture, in batches, through an electric blender or a food mill.
Stir in the sour cream or yogurt, the dill, lemon rind and mace.
To serve cold, chill several hours.
To serve hot, return to heat through.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sliced cookies(over 100 years old)
directions: Mix as other cookies, then to first 2 cups flour (plain), add soda, salt, cinnamon, vanilla and nuts.
Keep adding flour until you have a stiff enough dough to shape into a loaf.
Work on a molding board to shape into a loaf.
(Makes 3 or 4 loaves).
Wrap into wax paper and chill.
Slice thin and bake until light brown at 350°.
Keep in airtight container.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mash bananas and add to mixture; add eggs, one at a time, mixing between each.
Sift flour and spices 3 times.
Fold dry ingredients into banana mixture.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Take out when
center of each loaf is barely moist. Adjust as needed.
The whole house will smell great!

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix with 1/4 pound melted butter.
Line 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan with crumbs.
Reserve 1/2 cup for top.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large pan, brown onions in margarine until tender.
Add beef broth, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; bring to a boil. Place in large or individual baking dishes.
Top each with a slice of toasted bread and slice of cheese.
Place under broiler to melt cheese.

title: grandma henry's peanut butter candy
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until a soft ball forms.
Remove from stove.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: helen's chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound meat until 1/4-inch thick.
Place ham and cheese on each piece of chicken.
Roll-up carefully beginning at narrow end. Secure with toothpicks.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Mix hamburger, seasoning salt, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and liquid smoke.
When mixed up, make about 6 hamburger patties.
Tear off aluminum foil big enough to put one hamburger patty, one slice of onion and some potatoes and carrots.
Wrap it up with foil and put it on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sauteed peppers
directions: Saute peppers in 1/2 the oil until they start to brown.
Add remaining oil, salt, sherry and wine vinegar; simmer 15 minutes. Chill.
Serves 2.
Nice with sandwiches.

title: chickpeas in tomato sauce
directions: Add wine and continue to simmer, stirring occasionally until mixture thickens into a sauce, about 14 minutes.
Stir in chickpeas and 3/8 cup feta cheese, crumbled.
Stir until cheese melts, about 4 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and let sit 10 minutes before serving.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Heat about 1-inch of oil in a skillet to 375°.
Beat eggs well in large mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Holding opening of funnel covered with finger, pour 1/4 cup batter into wide mouth funnel.
Run batter into hot oil using a slow wide circular motion and maintaining a steady stream. Fry, turning once, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serve warm.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix 3 soups together.
Pour half into bottom of casserole dish.
Place wet rice (uncooked) over this and cover with remainder of soup.
Place cut up chicken over this mixture and sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic.
Over this, pour a little less than 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°. Can be made ahead and refrigerated until baking time.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and sugar. Blend together eggs, oil and 5 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice.
Add to sifted ingredients.
Add the pumpkin and nuts.
Pour into 4 greased and floured coffee cans or loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: noodles florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
In medium saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour and salt, blended with milk.
Bring to the boiling point, then simmer, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes. Stir in cheese, stirring constantly, until melted.
In greased 2-quart oblong baking dish, layer 1/2 the noodles, then spinach, mushrooms and 1/2 sauce.
Top with remaining noodles and sauce; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until bubbling.
Makes about 8 side dish servings.

title: mom's greek green beans
directions: Fry bacon and onion until bacon is crispy.
Drain.
Add green beans and tomato sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: rainbow jello salad
directions: For each layer dissolve Jell-O (1 package) in 1 cup boiling water.
Divide mixture in half.
In one half add 1/3 cup sour cream; stir slowly.
Pour in bowl or pan and refrigerate until firm.
In the other half add 3 tablespoons water and set aside. When first half is firm, add the other half and refrigerate until firm.
Repeat for each box of Jell-O.

title: chili verde casserole
directions: Spray 3-quart casserole.
Then spray each tortilla with Pam and place in microwave to soften.
Line casserole with tortillas, if desired quarter additional tortillas and line the sides of dish. Split (can leave seeds in) and lay chilies on top of tortillas. Sprinkle cheeses on top of chilies.
Mix eggs, flour and milk; beat well.
Pour over cheeses.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes then at 325° for 15 minutes.
Serve with favorite side dishes.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Fry ground beef, pepper and onion together; drain.
Pour pinto beans in a large casserole dish.
Pour ground beef mixture over beans.
Pour barbecue sauce over beef and beans.
Sprinkle cheese over barbecue sauce.
Stir up corn meal mix and pour over top of all.
Bake until bread is done at 350°.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Top with 1/2 cup coconut, reserved, and add a few cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: shrimp and seafood leg casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together thoroughly in a 4-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mushroom spinach strata(breakfast - brunch)
directions: Grease a 10-inch quiche or pie pan and set aside.
In a saucepan, melt the butter and saute the mushrooms for about 5 minutes.
Remove the mushrooms with a slotted spoon and set aside. Add the chopped onion to the pan; saute for 5 minutes and remove pan from heat.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix together and bake in a 250° oven for 3
hours.
Before eating, take cover off 1/2 hour to brown.

title: orange spiked zucchini and carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients in nonstick saucepan.
Cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes until zucchini is tender.
Uncover and simmer until most of the liquid has evaporated.

title: cold creamed zucchini soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine zucchini, chicken broth, scallions, salt, pepper and dill.
Cook mixture until soft, approximately 20-30 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and sour cream in a blender or food processor until smooth.
Add zucchini mixture, a portion at a time, and process until smooth.
Chill overnight or until very cold.
Garnish with chopped chives or paprika.
Serves 8.

title: my favorite chocolate cookie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, margarine and chocolate; add eggs, one at time, until well blended.
Mix in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add gradually to chocolate mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Cover and chill 2 hours or overnight.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonful into confectioners sugar, coating lightly; shape into a kiss. Place on greased baking sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 14 minutes or until done.
Remove from baking sheets and place on wire racks to cool.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook giblets until done. Saute celery and onion until transparent. Add bread cubes, cornbread and seasoning.
Pour reserved broth over ingredients. Stir lightly to blend.
Stuff cavity of turkey. Roast as directed.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: wedding punch
directions: Cook to dissolve sugar and water; let cool.
Mix orange juice and pineapple juice with sugar and water.
Freeze in covered containers.
Let set out 2 to 3 hours until slushy.
Then add ginger ale.
Makes about 30 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all well and make balls.
Roll in nuts and parsley, or just nuts.

title: peppermint ice cream pie
directions: Place softened ice cream into the crust.
Let freeze hard. To serve, top each slice with whipped topping and chocolate syrup.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Combine yeast and 1/2 cup warm milk in a 2-cup liquid measuring cup.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine yeast, 1 cup milk and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Gradually add 1 cup flour; stir until smooth.
Gradually add flour to make soft dough. Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let stand in a warm place (85°) for 15 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all items in small baking casserole dish.
Cut hearts if necessary.
This dip should be served hot and thick.
Serve with crackers.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chinese chicken salad ii
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put into greased 9 x 13 baking dish.

title: gofer cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour margarine over mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip cookies into this and let dry on waxed paper.

title: cranberry nut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a 9-inch pie plate (or decorative quiche plate).
Lay cranberries on bottom of plate; sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
In a medium bowl, beat egg until thick.
Add sugar gradually.
Stir in flour and melted butter.
Mix well.
(If needed, add teaspoon of water to thin batter.)
Pour batter over cranberries in swirls.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown. Serve with vanilla ice cream.
Enjoy!
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: coleslaw
directions: Dice cabbage, carrot, onion and pepper.
Place in blender (ingredients won't fit into blender at the same time, so you need to do it in 2 to 3 batches).
Add enough water to cover vegetables; cover blender and grate until vegetables are finely chopped.
Drain thoroughly.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour; measure, then re-sift with baking powder, soda and salt.
Add shortening and butter; mix into dry ingredients until coarse consistency.
Pour in buttermilk.
Stir together good. Knead with small amount of flour.
Pinch into small balls and pat to roundness.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in preheated oven at about 450° for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 1 1/2 to 2 dozen small biscuits.

title: six-cup fruit salad
directions: Drain orange slices.
Mix together ingredients and chill. This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: marinated chicken sauce
directions: For every 4 pieces of chicken, cover and marinate with all the ingredients.

title: garlic shrimp and pasta
directions: In a saucepan, mix cornstarch, broth, garlic, parsley, lemon juice and pepper. Over medium-high heat, heat to a boil. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly. Add shrimp. Cook 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink, stirring often. Toss with spaghetti. Serves 4.

title: dilis with chili(anchovy)
directions: Fry dilis in oil until crispy enough.
Set aside and use leftover oil to saute onion until golden brown and aromatic.
Add chopped tomatoes, sugar, pepper and salt; let simmer until all water is practically gone, except oil left with tomatoes.
Add crispy dry anchovies.
Cool and keep in airtight bottle to keep it crispy.
Use as an appetizer.

title: baked steak
directions: Pound flour into steak on both sides.
Melt fat in skillet; brown well on both sides.
Place in baking dish.
Add onion and tomatoes.
Add enough water to cover meat.
Cover with tight lid. Bake in a 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hershey pie
directions: Fold whip cream into chocolate as quickly as possible. Then pour into crust. Place in freezer to set.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks.
Place on large piece of Reynolds Wrap.
Mince approximately one clove of fresh garlic over potatoes.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and oregano.
Dot with butter.
Pour 3 tablespoons of olive/vegetable oil on top.
Seal foil tightly.
Cook on grill 10 to 15 minutes on each side until tender when poked with a fork.

title: busy day meat loaf
directions: Make your favorite meat loaf recipe and roll out in rectangle. Lay slices of precooked boiled ham and Mozzarella cheese on it. Roll up and place in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: tom and jerry batter
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff.
Add sugar while beating.
Beat yolks and add to whites.
Add vanilla and soda.
One teaspoon nutmeg can be added if desired.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine last five ingredients in a jar with a lid; shake well and chill.
Thoroughly wash spinach; drain well and tear into bite-size pieces.
Chill in tight plastic bag to crisp.
Combine spinach and mushrooms in large bowl; toss with dressing.
Garnish with sunflower seeds.

title: cool rise sweet rolls
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, dry yeast, sugar and salt in large bowl. Stir well to blend.
Add the softened butter.
Add hot water to ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl.
Add the slightly beaten egg and 1/2 cup more of flour.
Beat with mixer at high speed for 1 minute or until elastic, scraping bowl.
Stir in remaining flour gradually with wooden spoon.
Use enough flour to make a soft dough which leaves the sides of bowl.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts, and beat with mixer. Add nuts and pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: eggplant neopolitan(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake frozen spinach for 30 minutes. Saute eggplant in oil until golden and drain on paper towel. Combine eggs with all cheeses.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix tomato sauce with Italian seasoning and spread on the bottom of pan.
Place a layer of eggplant on top of sauce.
Spread with cheese mixture.
Top with souffle to cover cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let set before serving.
(May be frozen before or after cooking.)

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: punch
directions: Mix.
Put ginger ale in just before serving.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Sift and mix all ingredients.
To serve, use 3 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup of water.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Melt butter in skillet and saute onions, celery, parsley and mushrooms.
Pour over stuffing mix in large bowl. Toss together well.
Pour in enough broth to moisten; add beaten eggs and mix together well.
Pack lightly in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high for 5 minutes, then reduce to low for 4 to 8 hours.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and salt until lemon colored.
Blend well. Fold in coconut.
Add softened butter, flour and milk.
Put in crust and top with rest of coconut.
Bake.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream butter and sifted sugar.
Knead for a long time until mixture is very stiff.
Add vanilla.
Wait until it is rather crumbly after mixing; add a few drops of milk, a little at a time, until mixture is thickened smooth.
Drain cherries.
Take a level teaspoonful of fondant in hand; flatten into a cup shape and place cherry in middle.
Smooth over cherry.
Place on waxed paper in refrigerator for 20 to 30 minutes.
Melt paraffin wax and chocolate together.
Take cherry filled fondant and dip in chocolate.
Place on wax paper.

title: creamy minted mocha
directions: In food processor or blender container, crush peppermint candy. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate cherry cheese cake cups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line 24 muffin cups with paper baking cups. Slice well chilled cookie dough into 24 slices. Place slices in bottom of muffin cups.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip until well mixed.
Pour in cooked pie shell.
Freeze overnight.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef, add onions and taco seasoning.
Mix together all other ingredients, except chips and cheese.
Place meat mix in casserole dish and top with tortilla chips.
Pour in soup mixture next, then grated cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bean cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Heat greased skillet.
Spoon out mixture and brown over medium heat.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat sweet potatoes, sugar, milk, butter, eggs, salt and vanilla until smooth.
Transfer to a greased 2 qt. baking dish.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix eggs and brown sugar.
Add vanilla, Bisquick mix, pecans, coconut and raisins.
Bake in 2 square pans at 350° for 30 minutes. Cake sinks in the middle.
Cut when cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: emma's rice
directions: In a large, ovenproof skillet or casserole, brown crumbled sausage, rice and onion.
Drain as necessary.
Add the mushroom soup, celery, chicken, salt, pepper and water.
Cover; bake for about an hour at 300° to 325°.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except stuffing, in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with stuffing mix.
Bake in a 250° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: veal picatta
directions: Dredge cutlets in seasoned flour and brown in a small amount of hot oil. Saute mushrooms with garlic in small amount of butter. Arrange cutlets in baking pan; add beef stock and lemon juice to mushrooms and bring to a boil. Pour over cutlets; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's salad
directions: Combine both packages of Jell-O with the boiling water.
Let cool.
Add the remaining ingredients and let set until firm.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream together Ricotta cheese, cream cheese and sugar. Continue beating, adding eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla; fold in sour cream and then flour.
Blend well.
Pour into greased and floured spring-form pan.

Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. When done, turn off oven (don't open) and let cake set for 1 hour. When cake is completely cooled, remove from pan, wrap in foil and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Makes very large, thick cake!

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix and put in crust. Bake at 500° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake 1 hour.

title: cherry chewbilees
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and brown sugar, cut in shortening until fine crumbs form.
Stir in 1/2 c nuts and coconut.
Reserve 1/2 c crumb mixture.
Press into the bottom of a greased 9x13 inch pan.
Bake at 350 F for 12-15 minutes.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Combine and sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry stamps(tasty stickum)
directions: Will also need slick magazine, scissors, newspaper, saucepan, potholder and spoon.

title: oven hamburgers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, 1/2 cup of the soup and salt.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Shape into 6 patties.
Place in 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Blend together remaining soup, chili sauce and mustard; pour over patties.
Bake, covered, at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.
Serve patties on noodles. Stir sauce and spoon over patties.
Makes 6 servings.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together sugar, margarine, egg, almond extract, and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Divide dough into halves.
In one half, blend red food coloring.
Roll 1 teaspoon of each colored dough into a strip about 4 inches long. Place strips side by side, press lightly together and twist like a rope.
Place on cookie sheet.
Curve top down to form handle of cane.
Bake 9 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: tomato soup
directions: Mix everything together in a pot.
Cook on a low heat on stove for 5 minutes.

title: rhubarb pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Batter will be thick. Spread over bottom of well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry, blueberry crisp
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix the oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar and margarine; sprinkle over berries.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pea and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until lightly browned.
Add drained mushrooms.
Saute slightly.
Add sour cream, sugar and peas and liquid.
Simmer until it bubbles.
Pour in greased casserole.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour, eggs, buttermilk and lemon extract. Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: two faced chili
directions: Combine everything except meat. Bring to boil; let cool. Add browned meat and bring to boil. Add tomato juice for desired density of sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and put in casserole dish. Combine mayonnaise, soup, cheese and eggs.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Top with crackers.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Put
sugar,
salt and cream into a heavy pan.
Bring to boil for
minutes.
Take
off
stove.
Put
in butter and chocolate chips and beat fast with mixer.
Butter pan and pour in.
Let cool; cut the size you like.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter; cream in sugar and cocoa; cream in eggs.
Beat, then mix in Pet milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bird nest cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch and peanut butter together.
Stir in chow mein noodles.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Place raisins and chocolate chips in center, if desired.
Cool before serving.

title: bourbon street chocolate bread pudding
directions: In 1-quart saucepan over low heat, heat milk and chocolate pieces until milk is warm and chocolate pieces are softened, stirring occasionally.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in warm milk mixture, sugar and bourbon.
Place bread cubes in 1-quart casserole.
Pour milk mixture over bread; stir gently to coat. Place large shallow baking pan on middle rack of oven.
Carefully place casserole with mixture into baking pan.
Fill baking pan with hot water to depth of 1-inch.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: bananapops
directions: Melt the chocolate chips.
Roll the half banana in the chocolate, then roll in Rice Krispies.
Push a pop stick into each banana.
Cool and eat.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 7-inch ungreased pan with rolls. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes. Rolls will start to brown but not quite done. Cool.

title: cherry tart
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then take half of the mixture and put in a greased tart pan, then spread your fruit filling over dough.
Then crumble remaining dough mixture over the filling. Bake at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes.

title: almond fruited cheese ball
directions: In small bowl of electric mixer, combine cream cheese, raisins, coconut, pineapple, almond extract and 1/2 cup cereal. Mix well. Refrigerate at least 30 minutes. Form into ball. Just before serving, roll in remaining 1/4 cup cereal. Serve with crackers or fresh fruit.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet.
Cook and stir meat, onion and garlic in shortening until meat is brown and onion is tender. Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly; simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: run down
directions: Pour the lime juice over fish and set aside.
Cook the coconut milk in a heavy frying pan until it is oily.
Add the onion and garlic and cook until the onion is tender.
Add the hot pepper, tomatoes, salt, pepper, thyme and vinegar.
Stir and cook very gently for 10 minutes.
Drain fish; add the other ingredients and cook until the fish is tender, about 10 minutes.
Serve hot with boiled green bananas and boiled flour dumplings.
Run down can also be used as a stuffing for breadfruit.
Salt codfish or lobster can be substituted for mackerel.

title: oat bran fruit muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine oat bran, flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix thoroughly; set aside.
In a small bowl, lightly beat egg with a fork, then stir in milk, salad oil and grated peel.
Pour all at once into flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Fold in apples, dates and walnuts.
Fill 12 greased or paper cup lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until done, about 20 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake frosting
directions: Cook together 10 to 12 minutes.
Then, remove from heat and beat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Makes enough for top and middle.
(Double for sides.)

title: diabetic sugarless date cookies
directions: Mix together eggs, 2 tablespoons soda, liquid sweetener, 1 teaspoon soda and water.
Add first mixture.
Add flour and baking powder.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: overnight caramel rolls
directions: Let bread dough thaw slightly and break into pieces into buttered 13 x 9 x 2 cake pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding over dough. Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar and milk.
Pour over dough and sprinkle with cinnamon and nuts.
Place in cold oven overnight. In morning, turn oven to 350° (do not preheat).
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Invert onto cookie sheet lined with foil while hot.

title: corn bread salad
directions: When corn bread has cooled, crumble in bowl.
Add bacon, onion and pepper.
Add mayonnaise and mix.
Fold in the tomatoes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add water with juice; add dash of salt.
Stir in pie filling and pineapple; chill until firm. Mix softened cream cheese with Cool Whip.
You might need to add a little sugar and milk to make creamier and smoother.
Spread on top of Jello-O and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
You can use a 9 x 13 pan or serving bowl, your choice.

title: hymel's eggplant and seafood casserole
directions: In heavy saucepan, boil eggplant that has been peeled and cubed.
Cook for about 20 minutes, or until tender.
Drain and set aside for at least half an hour.
In same heavy pot add oil and saute shrimp about 10 minutes.
Add onions and saute over low fire for about 10 minutes.
Add eggplants and cook about 15 or 20 minutes.
Add bell pepper and cook for 15 minutes.
Then add 1 cup bread crumbs and cook for 15 minutes more.
Add crab meat; cook for 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Add extra bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° until hot through and through.

title: orange roughy with papaya salsa
directions: Salsa:
In a small bowl, combine papaya, almonds, onion, vinegar and red pepper; set aside.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Parboil zucchini and drain.
Slice lengthwise and arrange on cookie sheet.
Coat with canned milk.
Salt and pepper to taste and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tuna pate
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix all together until well mixed. Serve with crackers.

title: appetizers
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz and Bisquick and roll into a 1-inch roll. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Cut in slices.
Bake at 375°.
(Add sesame seed before baking, if desired.)

title: easy stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours, or place in crock-pot for 7 to 9 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: crumb-topped tomatoes
directions: Remove stems and cores from tomatoes.
Halve crosswise.
Place, cut side up, in baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, margarine, herbs, pepper and garlic or onion salt. Sprinkle atop tomatoes.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and put into hot jars.
Break up garlic and put 1 bud or more into each jar as well as a piece of hot pepper.
Boil the rest of ingredients and pour over okra.
Seal with hot lids.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Mix sugar and mustard.
Stir in vinegar, garlic powder and pepper.
Add kraut, green pepper, cucumbers and onions.
Chill about 2 hours before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Layer hash browns in bottom of casserole dish add sausage and 1/2 of cheese. Mix eggs and milk together. Pour over top and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: apple coconut cake
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix well.
Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.

title: potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cut in half and scoop out, leaving shell.
Fill shell with shredded cheese.
Top with diced bacon and strips of chili peppers.
Place under broiler for 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: oven popover-pancake with sausage and fried apple rings
directions: Beat eggs, salt, milk and flour until smooth.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In oven, melt butter in 9-inch cast-iron skillet or pie plate until sizzling hot; swirl to coat.
Immediately add batter; place in oven and bake for 20 minutes or until pancake is puffed, golden brown and firm.
Fill center with sausages and fried apple rings.
Cut in wedges and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: In large bowl combine first 5 ingredients.
Pour 1/2 bottle of barbecue sauce into mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into medium size balls; place in loaf pan.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°, covered. Uncover.
Pour a small amount of the remainder of barbecue sauce on top of each meatball.
Cook, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: salsa
directions: Place all but last ingredient in kettle and simmer 20 minutes. Remove 1/3 of mixture and place in blender.
Pour back into kettle and stir.
Add tomato paste.
Stir and simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 7 pints.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Coarsely chop cabbage and put in a 2-3 quart casserole dish or 9 x 13 pan.
Chop onion and sprinkle over cabbage.
Sprinkle desired amount of salt and pepper over cabbage and onions.
Mix mayo and soup together and spread over cabbage.
Sprinkle cheese over mayo mixture, then crackers, then melted margarine.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: grandma broesamle's lebkuickens cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Chill overnight.
Roll out on slightly floured board.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes in greased pan.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add bananas and eggs and beat until well mixed. Mix dry ingredients and blend with banana mixture, but do not overmix.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into 2 lightly greased loaf pans or a bundt pan.
Bake 55 minutes to 1 hour; test for doneness with a toothpick and cool on rack for 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Freezes beautifully.

title: brownie rounds
directions: Combine brownie mix, eggs and water in medium-size bowl; beat well.
Drop by teaspoons, 2 inches apart, on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 minutes or until firm.
Cool on sheets 1 minute; remove to racks.
Cool.
Frost, if desired.
Makes 4 dozen.
Nice alternative to brownies.
Enjoy!

title: tofu chili with beans
directions: Put aside beans and liquid.
Squeeze water from tofu and tear in pieces.
Combine next 7 ingredients in bowl.
Add to this tofu pieces and mix until coated.
Then fry tofu mixture in 1/4 cup oil over medium heat until all liquid is cooked out and tofu browned.

title: glorified hash browns
directions: In a large microwave safe bowl, combine the soup and cream cheese.
Cover and cook on high for 3-4 mins. or until cream cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add the potatoes and stir until coated.
Spoon into a greased 13x9x2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35-40 mins. or until the potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Bake 3-5 mins. longer or until cheese is melted.

title: sirloin roast
directions: Cut roast into cubes.
Add soups and water.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes; bake an additional hour at 350° (add more water if needed).

title: crab mousse
directions: Heat and blend cream cheese and mushroom soup.
Mix well with crab meat, mayonnaise, onion and celery.
Dissolve gelatine in water and blend into crab mixture.
Pour into a wet fish mold and chill overnight.
Decorate the fish with pimento, olive slices and parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup and salt.
Mix well.
Add butter and vanilla; beat well.
Put pecans on bottom of pie shell.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Lower to 300° and cook for 35 minutes longer.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix eggs and cooking oil; add oranges and mix well, then add cake mix.
Mix and bake in three layers.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: korean noodles (island style)
directions: In large pot, cook saimin in boiling water.
Rinse thoroughly under running water and chill in refrigerator.
Beat eggs in small bowl, adding sugar and salt.
Fry in pan and slice in thin strips. Combine saimin, char siu, cucumbers, bean sprouts and eggs and serve with sauce.

title: yummy gingerbread man
directions: Beat until well blended shortening and molasses.
Mix together and add salt, ginger, baking powder, cinnamon and flour.
Chill dough.
Roll out with rolling pin on floured board.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out cookies.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Use greased cookie sheet.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together; add egg yolk and mix well.
Add flour to butter mixture.
Melt the milk chocolate bar. Add melted chocolate bar, vanilla and walnuts to mixture.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until done.

title: cheese snack
directions: Spread small amount of butter on flour tortillas; top with pieces of cheese.
Place in microwave or oven just until cheese is melted.
Take out of oven and roll up immediately.
Let cool a while before eating.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: old-fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and cook until thickened well. Stir slowly while cooking.
Beat with mixer when cooked until smooth.
Pour into pie shell and top with whipped egg whites. Brown in 400° oven.

title: bernice heugatter's milk chocolate and peanut butter bars
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine peanut butter and margarine; beat until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy. Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup milk chocolate morsels. Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until edges begin to brown.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Combine
first	7
ingredients, stirring well.	Combine egg substitute	and evaporated skimmed milk;
add to the corn mixture. Spoon
mixture
into a 1 quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Place dish in a larger shallow pan; add water to a depth of 1 inch to pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a
knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield:
6 servings (102 calories per 1/2 cup serving).

title: aunt ila hemphill's veg-all casserole
directions: Mix; cook 30 minutes.
Top with 1 package soda crackers, crumbled.
Slice 1 stick margarine; arrange on top.
Return to oven and brown (about 10 minutes).

title: vegetable salad dressing-dip
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add milk slowly and stir vigorously.
If using for cole slaw or regular vegetable salad, use only enough milk to make it run over easy.
If using thinner as on lettuce and sliced, hard-boiled eggs, make thinner with more milk.
Add vinegar last, then stir again.
Will thicken some. Also great dip for finger veggies at parties.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Pour in fruit.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over fruit.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt butter with cocoa and mix.
Set aside to cool.

title: sundae cake (coca)
directions: Tear angel food cake into small pieces.
Mix Cool Whip and dry hot chocolate mix (1/2 cup) together.
Layer cake pieces and Cool Whip in bowl.
Mix together 1/2 cup hot chocolate mix and 2 1/2 tablespoons water.
Drizzle over cake mixture.
Cover with nuts and cherries.
Repeat layers and refrigerate.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and cream.
Add eggs; blend well. Sift flour and spices together.
Add 1/2 flour, then soda and water.
Mix well after reach addition.
Add ground raisins, then remaining flour.
Form dough into balls (about 1 tablespoon). Bake on greased sheets at 350°.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix by hand, well, until blended.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt or angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and twenty minutes depending on heat of your oven.
May use 1/2 cup chopped nuts if desired.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and put in greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Mix juices, pudding and Jell-O and cook on medium heat until gooey.
Add fruit and fold in Cool Whip.
Chill in a clear bowl because it is pretty!
Will be fluffy at first and then will settle flat on top.

title: lentil roast
directions: Mix well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Spray baking dish generously.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine 3/4 cup cornbread crumbs with cooked sausage, cheese, green pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Mix well and put in a greased pan.
Combine milk, eggs and 1/2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce. Stir until blended.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Combine remaining cornbread crumbs, butter and sauce.
Pour over mixture in pan.

title: quick turkey or chicken a la king
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, melt margarine.
Stir in flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo in a 10 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.

Mix all ingredients except Cheddar cheese. Grate half the Cheddar cheese and add to ingredients. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown. Grate the other half of the Cheddar cheese and sprinkle on top.
Let melt. Serve hot.

title: tropical frosting
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt and vinegar in a heavy saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until clear without stirring.
Cook until mixture forms a thin thread when dropped from spoon (242° on candy thermometer).
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add hot syrup, beating constantly.
Continue beating until frosting holds shape.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Spread frosting between layers.
Sprinkle coconut over top and sides.
Put freshly grated coconut over.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook onion in shortening until tender.
Add beef; cook until browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
