Simmer about 10 minutes. Serve between toasted split buns.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: In 8 Qt. Pot- cook chicken- strain and keep broth. Chop celery and onions and cook in broth. Dice chicken and add to pot. Cook until soft. Make a paste of cornstarch, molasses and soy sauce. Slowly add paste into pot. Serve over noodles.

title: dressed-up chicken
directions: Split 4 whole chicken breasts (about 4 pounds) and remove skin. You may bone them or leave bone in.
Arrange in a shallow type baking dish.
Cover breasts with thin slices of Swiss cheese.
Stir together the soup (undiluted) and wine.
Spoon over chicken. Sprinkle top with the stuffing mix.
Drizzle top with the butter. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 50 minutes.
Serves 8. You may leave the wine out.

title: piccalilli
directions: Put vegetables in a kettle in layers with salt sprinkled between.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water. Drain again.
Cook vegetables with sugar, vinegar, pickling spice and water until mixture has thickened slightly.
Pour into jars. Makes 7 quart jars.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream oleo; add peanut butter and cream well.
Add granulated sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add brown sugar and cream.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add flour and milk alternately to mixture, mixing well.
Roll soft dough into small balls the size of a walnut with floured hands.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: edie's punch
directions: Mix juices and sugar, pour over ice cubes; add sherbet by spoonful.
Add ginger ale; mix gently and garnish with lemon slices.
Serve at once.
Makes 3 quarts or 24 servings.
You may add white wine or vodka.

title: chicken long rice
directions: Heat oil in heavy saucepan. Stir-fry ginger root, garlic and chicken until lightly browned.
Add water and mushrooms.
Cook for about 45 minutes or until chicken is tender. Add salt, pepper, m.s.g. and curry.
Cook for 15 minutes. Stir in long rice and onions.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 regular people or 3 Hawaiians.

title: fancy macaroni and cheese
directions: Follow directions to macaroni and cheese.
When done, add tomatoes, peas, and hot dogs.
Cook in microwave for an additional 10 minutes.

title: special guest cookies
directions: Cream margarine
and sugar;
add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, soda
and
cream of tartar; add oatmeal and nuts. Roll dough into
cookie size balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake about 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle small orange Jell-O with cottage cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes and then mix other ingredients.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray pizza pan with Pam.
Spread crescent rolls in pizza pan.
Crumble sausage and bacon on top. Spread hash browns over meat layer.

title: pam's no bake cheesecake
directions: One at a time mix together cream cheese, sugar, sour cream, vanilla flavoring and Cool Whip.
Mix well until no lumps appear. Pour mixture into graham cracker pie shell.
Last but not least, gently add fruit topping of choice on top of mixture.
Cover and let chill for approximately 4 hours.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread; don't let rise.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Tear 1 loaf into pieces.
Drop helter-skelter in pan.
Melt butter; add rest of ingredients.
Heat and mix until smooth.
Pour over bread in pan.
Tear second loaf and toss on top.
Let raise 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with vegetable tray.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Brown chops. Place in large casserole. Top with remaining ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° from 1-2 hours or until tender. Serves 4-6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and top with 1 stick melted margarine and corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: southern fried fish
directions: Slice fish as you like or cook small ones whole.
Salt and pepper both sides of fish; beat egg in milk.
Fix a double layer paper bag.
Mix meal and flour in bag.
Dip fish in milk and egg mixture and drop in sack of meal mix.
Shake to coat; drop in hot oil.
Be sure oil is boiling before dropping in fish.
Cook several at a time; pieces will float to top when done.
Cook to golden brown.

title: grandma jane's bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl blend sugar, Crisco and eggs.
In another bowl put Nabisco 100% Bran and hot water.
To first mixture add buttermilk, salt, soda, flour, oatmeal and All-Bran.
Add Bran and water mixture.
Bake in muffin tins at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Can make fresh daily as batter will keep, refrigerated, up to 3 weeks.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and toss with warm broccoli.
Cover and chill.

title: midwestern chowder
directions: Mix all but half and half until cheese melts and heat to boil. Add half and half.

title: henny kenny casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter.
Mix soup and add corn, then cheese and meat.
Cook macaroni in broth.
Combine all ingredients and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
This makes 2 casseroles.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs; add vanilla and buttermilk.
Add flour mixture, banana and nuts.
Grease pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or more if needed.

title: stuffed cabbage with sauerkraut
directions: Parboil cabbage head.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix ground beef, sauteed onion, salt, pepper and rice together.
Separate leaves from head, being careful not to break them.
Place large spoonful of mixture in center of leaf; fold around it.
Place sauerkraut in bottom of large pot, then place stuffed cabbage on top of sauerkraut, folded side of cabbage leaf down.
Add enough tomato sauce and water to cover cabbage rolls.
Bring to slight boil, then turn to medium heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: unsweetened muffins
directions: Sift flour; measure 2 cups.
Add baking powder, salt and sugar; mix well.
Sift into a mixing bowl.
Beat egg until foamy, then stir in milk and melted shortening.
Add to flour mixture, stirring only until mixed, not smooth.
With spoon, dip batter into muffin pans.
Bake in a 425° oven for 25 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients; shape into a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: nestle toll house pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a large baking pan (or use Pam).
In small bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Spread into baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes; cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 35 (2-inch) squares.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine (half or all of margarine can be replaced with equal amount of applesauce for lower fat) and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips. Spread evenly over a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ugali
directions: Ugali is maize meal or corn meal poured into boiling water and stirred into a stiff mush.
The Kenyans prefer white meal.
This might be eaten daily and sometimes the only meal they get.
Very filling!!

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until done.
It will be better the next day.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine eggs and milk in an 8-quart saucepot.
Blend sugar, flour and salt in medium size mixing bowl.
Stir into egg mixture. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until custard coats the spoon, about 15 minutes.
Do not let custard boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
When mixture has cooled, freeze in ice cream freezer following manufacturer's directions.

title: clam chowder
directions: Do not dilute soups and do not drain clams.
Combine soups, clams and cream in 6-quart pan and heat, stirring occasionally until hot.
Do not boil.
Garnish with pepper and parsley.
Can be made in a crock-pot on low for 6 hours.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat jello, water and marshmallows in pan until boiling.
Set aside and let cool.
Mix together Dream Whip (follow directions on box), crushed pineapple, sour cream and nuts with the jello mixture.
Put in large container and refrigerate.

title: lemon sponge cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together in bowl. Add in order:
oil, egg yolks, water, lemon juice and rind.
Beat with spoon.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until very, very stiff.
Pour egg yolks gradually over whipped egg whites, carefully folding just until blended.
Pour immediately into ungreased 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes. Invert cake.
When cold, loosen sides with spatula and remove cake from pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook onion and hamburger together, drain.
Put in crock-pot. Add other ingredients.
Cover and cook on low for two hours.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Cook and stir milk, sugar, egg yolks, margarine and vanilla over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes. Add coconut and pecans. Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: cowboy clam chowder
directions: Saute 2 pieces of chopped bacon or 2 patties of chopped sausage with
onion
in
a	large saucepan.
Add can of potato soup, juice
from
cans of clams and garlic powder.
Simmer for 10	minutes
then
add
cans
drained
clams and simmer another 5 minutes.	Serve with oyster crackers.

title: strawberry cheesecake pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions.
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar (2 teaspoons).
Beat until smooth; spread into bottom of cooled crust.
Puree half of the strawberries.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk and then mix in Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 12-inch dish, place a layer of graham crackers, then half the pudding mixture, then add another layer of graham crackers.
Add the rest of the pudding mixture.
Use the pie filling as a topping.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: rothan's dessert
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, baking powder and pecans.
Fold in cracker crumbs and pour into ungreased pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix Dream Whip, cream cheese and pineapple together to prepare topping.
When dessert is cooled, frost with topping.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken in white wine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip cutlets in Egg Beaters, then into bread crumbs.
Quickly brown cutlets in oil, then drain.
Put cutlets into large glass or metal baking dish and pour broth and wine over the cutlets.
Sprinkle sliced mushrooms over pan ingredients.
Cook for 50 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mallow popcorn balls
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler; add marshmallows and melt, blending well.
Pour over popcorn and stir.
Wet hands in cold water and form into balls, pressing together lightly.
Wrap individual balls in plastic wrap to store.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare vegetables according to directions on package.
Drain. In a pan, heat soup, cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until cheese melts.
Combine vegetables and sauce; add mushrooms and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place corn flakes and spices in plastic bag and crush.
Sprinkle crushed flakes on top of casserole and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until sauce bubbles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sauerbraten and potato dumpling
directions: Rub meat thoroughly with salt and pepper.
Place with onion, bay leaves and peppercorns into deep dish.
Do not use metal dish.
Heat equal parts vinegar and water and add sugar.
Pour while hot over meat to cover.
Cover dish well and refrigerate for 3 to 4 days.
Turn meat daily.

title: almond joy balls
directions: Melt chocolate bark and milk in a double boiler on low heat.

title: granola
directions: Mix oatmeal, raisins, coconut and walnuts in a large bowl. In another bowl, mix the honey, oil and vanilla.
Put dry ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Evenly distribute honey/oil mixture over top of dry ingredients.
Stir together to evenly coat.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Stir all together & pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: dark bread
directions: Raise once; put in pans.
Raise 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove.
Brown ground beef in bacon drippings along with onion, garlic, green pepper and celery; drain.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 30 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Garnish with bacon bits.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: *Beef and pork should be ground together.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well. Roll into balls the size of a quarter. Freeze 1 hour.
Melt together the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Stick toothpicks in balls and dip in chocolate mixture. Let drain on waxed paper.

title: cheesecakes
directions: Use cupcake liners.
Put a vanilla wafer in each cupcake liner. Mix all remaining ingredients in blender or mixer.
Put 2 tablespoons of filling in each cup.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Immediately put pie filling over each cheesecake (about 1 tablespoon).
Cool and refrigerate.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple.
Put in casserole dish.
Crumble crackers and mix with butter.
Put on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Especially good with ham.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, syrup, butter and salt in an electric frypan.
Heat to 350° until dissolved.
Turn heat to 400°.
Add peanuts and stir constantly until lightly brown (about 7 minutes). Sprinkle baking soda onto candy. Turn off.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet. Grease bottom of spoon and spread evenly.
Let cool, then store in covered container.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Whisk, blend or shake all ingredients until smooth.
Add to finely chopped cabbage and grated carrots.
Dressing will keep in refrigerator for a couple of weeks.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend well and roll in paprika or chopped parsley. Serve room temperature.
May also be made into rolls.

title: chicken schnitzel
directions: Dip chicken breasts in flour to coat.
Then dip in egg (scrambled), then put chicken in breadcrumbs mixed with cheese. Pound with hand to coat.
In frying pan, put 1/4 cup oil.
When oil is hot (small piece of breadcrumbs sizzle), add chicken breasts.
Fry each side about 5 to 10 minutes.
Turn when lightly brown.
Serve immediately.
Tastes great with a little lemon juice sprinkled over or salsa!

title: coconut pie filling
directions: Cook in microwave until bubbly, stirring with a whisk every 2 minutes.
Cook until thickens.
Add margarine and coconut.
Set aside to cool.

title: hamburger pot pie
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add tomato soup.
Mix together, then top with can of drained garden peas. Mix the 2 packages of instant potatoes according to directions and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese on top and put back in oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: meal-in-a-casserole
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving juice.
Layer ground beef, potatoes, onions, peas, tomatoes and seasoning in 8 x 11-inch casserole. Add tomato juice as needed to prevent dryness during baking.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: perfect pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and salt. Blend in egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with sour cream.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Use a 10-inch tube pan.
Cool in pan 30 minutes before turning out on a rack.

title: cornlight bread
directions: Mix well and bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: one dish chicken bake
directions: Mix contents of vegetable/seasoning packet, hot water and butter in large bowl until butter is melted. Stir in stuffing crumbs just until moistened. Let stand 5 minutes. Place chicken down center of 12 x 8 baking dish. Mix soup and sour cream or milk; pour over chicken. Spoon some of the stuffing over chicken. Spoon remaining stuffing along both sides of chicken.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Garnish with fresh sage leaves and flowers.

title: meat loaf with cheese sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cheese, milk and mustard in small saucepan. Heat on low until smooth.
Put aside 3/4 cup of this sauce.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup sauce and remaining ingredients in large bowl until well blended.
Shape into a loaf in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes.
Serve with reserved cheese sauce over it.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix well flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and shortening.
Add egg, bananas, chocolate chips and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: christmas ribbon salad
directions: This 3 layer salad looks pretty in a glass dish.
Prepare the 2 packages of lime jello according to directions on box.
Cool until almost set.
Dissolve the lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cut up marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice and 1 package cream cheese.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in 1 cup pineapple.
Cool slightly.
Fold in whipped cream and 1 cup mayonnaise.
Chill until thickened.
Pour over lime jello.
Make cherry jello according to package directions.
Chill until syrupy and pour over pineapple layer.
Chill until firm.
Takes a 9 x 15 x 1 1/2-inch pan.

title: no cook mints
directions: Mix all together until smooth.
Shape and store in a cool place.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Add rice, onions, celery, bell pepper, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until rice is done and vegetables are tender.
Add Ro-Tel, tomato soup and tomatoes.
Add both cheeses to mixture.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Stir occasionally.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook broccoli in 1 cup water.
Do not drain.
In blender, put milk, cheese and flour.
Cover and process at grind.
Add mixture to broccoli.
Add the half and half.
Cook, stirring frequently over medium heat until hot and mixture thickens.
Serve garnished with croutons.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside. Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add buttermilk, mixing well. Add yeast mixture; mix until dough forms a ball.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: frozen pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and freeze for 6 hours.

title: chicken bride and groom
directions: Cover chicken breasts with water in large pot.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Debone and tear into small pieces.
Spray an oblong baking dish with Pam.
Put chicken in dish.
Saute onion and celery in 1/2 stick margarine.
Pour over chicken.
Mix together sour cream and soup.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix lightly over top.
Melt remaining margarine and drizzle over stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: festive potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on. Peel and cube.
While still warm add oil, salt and vinegar.
Chill for 1 hour.
Then add olives, cabbage, pickles, carrots, pimento, bell pepper, mayonnaise, mustard and black pepper. Mix well.

title: chocolate pecan meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In medium bowl, beat egg whites at high speed until soft peaks form.
Beat in sugar, a little at a time, until stiff peaks form.
Do not scrape sides of bowl during beating.
Beat in vinegar and vanilla.
Fold in nuts and chocolate bits.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: In a frying pan (2-inches high), add butter.
As butter is melting, add heavy cream and stir.
Add chicken broth and egg yolks.
Add Prosciutto and half Locatelli.
Cook on medium/low heat until a nice thick consistency.
Add cooked pasta.
Top with remaining Locatelli.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Mix the first four ingredients; beat until well blended.
Mix eggs, cottage cheese, salt and spinach.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with a little tomato sauce mixture.
Layer the lasagne noodles, cheese mixture, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese, tomato sauce mixture and repeat.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This may be made the day before.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sweeten to your own taste.

title: fruited macaroni slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, sugar, mustard and salt; mix well.
Stir in cooked macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Mix well and cover.
Chill thoroughly.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Salt cucumbers and onions thoroughly; put in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours.
Drain water off.
Mix sugar and vinegar.
Blend so sugar dissolves.
Add 1/4 cup of water if it tastes too much like vinegar.
Add sour cream.
Add more sour cream for creamier taste. Serves 8.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except M&M's.
After mixture is mixed well, fold in M&M's.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned.

title: sweet-sour luncheon meat
directions: Bring water and carrots to a boil in skillet.
Cook, covered, until almost tender.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Stir together reserved juice, brown sugar, vinegar, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Add with pepper to skillet and stir until thickened.
Add meat and cook, covered, until heated through.
Serves 4.
May be served with rice or chow mein noodles.

title: pasta sausage salad
directions: Cook pasta; cool.
Add red pepper, green pepper, onion, olives, salami and pepperoni.
In small bowl, mix sour cream, mayonnaise and milk until smooth.
Add Parmesan cheese, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add to pasta mixture.
Toss and refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Steam broccoli.
Layer	chicken in 8-inch square baking dish. Cover with undiluted soup.	Place broccoli on soup, add cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts completely.

title: old fashioned buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar; stir in eggs, flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell. Bake until tip of knife inserted in the center comes out clean, about 45 to 60 minutes. Cool slightly before serving. Yields 8 servings.

title: ann's custard frosting
directions: On high speed, beat margarine, Crisco and sugar until fluffy and white.
Add 3 tablespoons flour, one at a time, until well blended.
Add slowly the milk; beat well.
Blend in vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Refrigerate.

title: harvest sweet potatoes
directions: Combine butter, sugar, salt, marmalade and wine in saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add raisins.
Arrange potatoes in shallow buttered casserole.
Cover with sauce.
Bake, covered, at 300° to 325° for 40 to 45 minutes. Yields 5 servings.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, beating until well blended. Sift dry ingredients.
Stir blended ingredients into dry ingredients until mixture is moist.
(Batter will be lumpy.) Grease muffin tins.
Fill tins 2/3 full with batter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix potato, salt and butter.
Work in as much powdered sugar as needed.
(Potato has moisture and will take more sugar than you think.)
Roll out, spread with peanut butter, roll up as jelly roll.
Cut.
Can be dipped in chocolate if desired.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix liquid ingredients together.
Add the liquid mixture to the dry mixture.
Mix well. Place in muffin pans and bake at 350° until done.
These muffins have no cholesterol and only 120 calories per muffin.

title: squid in tomato sauce(calamari al sugo)
directions: Peel squid and remove insides.
Cut off tentacles and heads. Pull out thin bone and wash well.
Slice tubes into 1/2 inch rings.
Parboil rings and peeled tentacles about 2 minutes and drain.
Saute onion and celery in olive oil.
Add garlic and brown lightly.
Mix in the squid and seasonings.
Blend well and brown 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and simmer 40 minutes or until tender.
A small amount of water can be added to thin sauce if desired.
Can be served over capellini or rice.

title: sunny tomato dressing
directions: Whiz in blender.
Add more water if needed to make a thinner consistency or more seeds to thicken.
The dressing will get thicker upon standing.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Top with pie filling. Refrigerate.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with fresh vegetable tray.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix together, adding milk gradually.
Bake in two 9-inch layer pans (I usually bake it in loaf pan).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until done.

title: strawberry pie filling
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil, then cut heat to medium-low and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add Jell-O.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Put sliced strawberries in baked pie shell and pour filling over berries.

title: aunt dink's homemade sauerkraut
directions: Cut up cabbage.
Pack jars within 3/4 inch with chopped or cut up cabbage.
Add 2 level teaspoons of plain salt to each jar. Fill to overflowing with boiling water.
Seal.
Place in pantry or storage area for several months before using.

title: nut cups
directions: To be made in 2 pans of small cupcake pans.

title: favorite corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add the milk and eggs and shortening; beat for 1 minute. Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bread is golden brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean broccoli and chop fine.
Peel the outer layers of the large broccoli stalks and discard.
Chop the inside portion of the stalks.
Fry diced bacon until crisp.
Drain all grease.
Chop red onion fine.
Combine broccoli, bacon and onion in a large bowl. Add sugar and vinegar to Miracle Whip and mix well.
Combine Miracle Whip mixture with broccoli mixture and mix well. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: kathy's fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in large pan.
Bring to rolling boil.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chips, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Stir until smooth. Pour into a large, greased pan.
Makes a big amount.

title: baked fish with mushrooms
directions: Cook mushrooms and
onions
in	bacon
drippings
until tender.
Sprinkle fish with salt
to taste and place in baking dish.
Combine mushrooms, onions, butter and tarragon.
Spread over fish.	Sprinkle with paprika.	Bake
at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Garnish with bacon bits.	Makes 4 servings.

title: chow mein
directions: Using chicken, pork or steak, saute celery and onion in butter.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: royal cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in hot water.
Let chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in cranberry sauce, celery and nuts.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into 1 qt. mold and chill until firm.

title: ham stuffed chicken breast supreme
directions: In medium sized bowl, combine bread cubes, cheese, deviled ham, green onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Add hot water; toss gently.
Place chicken breasts between pieces of waxed paper. Pound very thin with rolling pin or mallet.
Do not tear flesh. Place equal amount of stuffing in center of each breast.
Bring edges together, envelope style, and press to seal.
Place sealed-side-down in greased baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle evenly over top of stuffed chicken breasts and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serves 6.

title: apple dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla; mix well. Serve with strawberries, bananas, apples, oranges or kiwi.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook at 300° until passes toothpick test in 3 or 4 cake pans.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt together over low heat.
Pour over 6 quarts of popped corn.
Shape into balls.

title: pumpernickel dip
directions: Remove tops of loaves, pumpkin style.
Hollow out into bowls. Cut pieces from inside into 1 to 1 1/2-inch chunks, to be dipped later.
Combine remaining ingredients for dip.
Fill empty "bread bowls" with dip.

title: easy chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Season chicken very little with Tony's seasoning or any other "all season."
Wrap one slice of ham around each chicken breast.
Spray an oblong casserole dish with Pam. Pour entire can of soup at bottom of dish and smooth out evenly. Place chicken breasts on top of soup.
Bake for 30 minutes. Remove dish from oven.
Evenly distribute cheese on top of each chicken breast.
Bake for another 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Baste each breast with juices from pan before serving. Enjoy!

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into 2 loaves.
Wrap in plastic wrap and leave in refrigerator 24 hours.
Unwrap and place on rack.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool and slice.

title: date loaf
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk.
Boil, stirring occasionally until hard boil stage is reached.
Remove from heat; add dates and pecans.
Beat until creamy.
Form into roll on a damp cloth.
Roll and let cool.
Slice to serve.

title: miss eva's lemon chess pie
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar. Beat in eggs.
Stir in lemon juice and grated rind.
Pour into crust. Bake in oven at 400° for 10 minutes. Turn oven down to 325° and bake for 20 more minutes. Remove when firm and brown.

title: eggless rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water until tender and dry.
Add milk, sugar, raisins, marshmallows and vanilla.
Pour into a greased baking dish and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 350° oven until it starts to set in the center, about 40 minutes.
Serve either warm or cold with cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ooie-gooie cake
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine, 1 egg and nuts.
Press into rectangular pan.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Blend until smooth.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy cornbread dressing
directions: Wilt onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Mix canned soups and eggs.
Add this to wilted bell pepper and onion.
Mix well.
Pour in medium size pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 35 or 45 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook elbow macaroni and drain.
Set aside.
Mix in large bowl the green pepper, onion and pimentos.
Set aside.
Mix (in food processor or mixer) the soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Add to green pepper mixture.
Add macaroni.
Add 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese to mixture; stir together.
Put in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour, mixing at low speed until blended.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Prick with fork; bake 25 minutes until edges are light golden brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and mix with soup and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1/2 can of onion rings.
Pour mix in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle rest of onion rings on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Melt butter in frypan.
Add onion, pepper and garlic.
Saute low about 5 minutes until tender. Turn off heat.
Add in minced clams (include liquid).
Stir in bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Transfer mixture into ovenproof casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.
Enjoy!

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place Tater Tots in bottom of dish. Fry vegetable steaks or scallops and cut up in bite size pieces. Place on top of Tater Tots.
Next, add onions and mushrooms (if desired).
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Dissolve cocoa with 1 cup warm water.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake in layers.

title: ground beef - wild rice casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in a small amount oil.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add liquid.
Mix with spoon. Fill greased tins or lined tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cilantro pesto
directions: In a blender, combine cilantro (leaves only), lime juice, water, Parmesan, garlic, salt and pepper. Puree until smooth.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature to soften.
Combine cheeses, lemon juice, garlic powder and red pepper; beat with electric mixer or rotary beater until light and fluffy.
Stir in nuts; shape into a roll about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Sprinkle roll with paprika.
Chill.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: aunt ethel's dinner rolls(never fail)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of the scalded milk, having allowed milk to cool to warm (110° to 115°).
Add 1/2 cup flour to dissolved yeast and beat thoroughly.
Then add remaining milk (cooled to lukewarm), sugar and half of the flour.
Again beat until well mixed.
Add melted butter, the beaten egg and salt. Mix well.
Blend in remaining flour and turn onto floured board. Knead until dough feels smooth and elastic.

title: chess cake
directions: Beat together cake mix, 1 egg and margarine; spread into 13 x 8-inch buttered pan. (Pat into pan with hands.) Beat together 1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla; spread over first layer. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. (Cake will fall just like a chess pie.)

title: clams casino
directions: Put in a foil pan and broil for 5 minutes.

title: cream of garlic soup
directions: Crush and chop garlic.
Heat oil in heavy large saucepan over low heat.
Add garlic and cook until just beginning to color, stirring frequently.
Add broth and wine and bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add milk, cream and potato and simmer 30 minutes.

title: dixie's drumsticks
directions: Discard wing tips.
Cut remainder of each wing into 2 servings at the joint.
Put flour mix in 1 bowl and melted butter in another bowl.
Roll each piece of chicken in butter then in flour mix.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Make sure no pieces are touching.
Add remaining butter to pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven.
Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add eggs and mix.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well and pour in pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow fudge nutty bars
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9 pan.
In large bowl combine cake mix, brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine at low speed till crumbly.
Add milk and egg, stir until blended.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 - 30 minutes or until bars are set.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with marshmallows.
Return to oven 1 - 2 minutes or until marshmallows begin to puff.
Cool while preparing frosting.

title: nut butter balls
directions: Mix butter with granulated white sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts. Mix well and chill for 30 minutes. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll baked balls into confectioners sugar while warm.

title: orange pineapple jello
directions: Mix pineapple and jello in saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes. Cool.
Stir in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: nellie meyer's chocolate cake
directions: Cream together butter or shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, chocolate, milk, baking powder and flour.
Mix well and pour in layer pans or a sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eggplant and rice provencale
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat oil in large skillet over high heat.
Add eggplant cubes, stirring constantly.
Add next five ingredients.
Continuing to stir, add tomatoes.
Lower heat and cook until vegetables are tender, about 7 minutes.
Stir in rice and chicken broth.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Dot with butter. Bake, uncovered, for about 40 minutes.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Combine butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, sour cream, rum and almond extract, mixing well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with mashed bananas, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in pecans.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease sides and bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour rice evenly over bottom of pan.
Arrange salted and peppered chicken on top of rice.
Blend soup, water and onion soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown the meat. Drain off grease.
Mix all other ingredients together with meat.
Heat on low.
Serve as dip for nacho chips.

title: fish boil
directions: Place potatoes and 8 quarts water in kettle with the vents open.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1 cup salt and the onions.
Cook for 20 minutes, reducing heat to produce a steady roll action boil with cover vents still open.
(Begin timing when water returns to a boil.)
Place fish in the basket and lower into the water on top of the potatoes and onions.
Add remaining 1 cup salt.
Cover and bring to a gently rolling boil for approximately 12 minutes.
To test for doneness, spear potato with a fork, it will penetrate easily if done.
Fish is cooked when it flakes easily with a fork. Cooking time may vary a few minutes either way depending on the size of the potatoes and thickness of the fish steaks.
Skim off the fish oils before lifting out the fish.
Lift out basket with fish; drain water off potatoes and onions.
Serve with melted butter and lemon wedge.

title: butter rum sauce
directions: Cook butter and sugar until clear and bubbly.
Remove from heat and add egg, stirring constantly.
Add rum. Process in blender or food processor to make it very smooth.
Serve warm over bread pudding.
May be stored covered in refrigerator.

title: chicken lemon-dijon
directions: Combine breadcrumbs and lemon rind in a zip top plastic bag, shaking well to mix.
Combine mustard, lemon juice and lime juice; brush over both sides of chicken.
Place chicken in bag with breadcrumb mixture, shaking to coat.

title: chocolate punch
directions: Bring milk to a boil and add instant coffee (don't boil).
Set aside to cool.
Whip cream.
Mix vanilla and chocolate ice cream to manipulate.
Fold cool coffee, then whipped cream, into ice cream.
Add Dairy Queen right before serving.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: beef or chicken burritos
directions: Fry and drain tortillas in oil.
Spread 1/8 each of meat, cheese and refried beans on each tortilla.
Roll up and place in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts. Top with desired remaining ingredients.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Sift together cornmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Pour in baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Allow corn bread to cool.
Break into pieces.
Saute celery and onions in butter.
Add to bread along with spices. Moisten with turkey stock.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Make jello according to package directions.
Substitute juice from pineapple for water when making jello.
Mix all ingredients and mold.
Serve on platter with lettuce, fresh lime or pineapple slices.
May also be decorated with cherries.

title: portofino cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and wine.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Fold in pecans and turn into a 2-quart mold or bowl.
Chill until firm. Great with turkey and pork.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt, syrup and milk in pan.
Bring to boil slowly. Cook until it reaches soft ball stage when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat until creamy and losing gloss.
Pour into greased pan to cool.

title: shrimp stuffed celery
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Clean celery and cut into bite size pieces.
Stuff shrimp mixture into celery and chill.

title: chocolate maple-nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine flour, sugar and salt; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in 1 beaten egg. Press evenly into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: creamy chili dip
directions: Blend ingredients together until smooth.

title: parsley popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Coat a 12-muffin tin with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, salt, milk, cold water and chopped parsley.
With electric mixer at high, beat mixture until just smooth.
Fold softly beaten egg whites into batter; mix gently, then evenly fill prepared muffin cups with batter.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until well browned, puffed up and firm.

title: zasmazine soup(potato soup)
directions: Take potatoes and cut into chunks.
Cover with water.
Add 2 more cups of water, parsley, onion and celery if you like. Add allspice, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer until potatoes are well done.

title: ham croquettes
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour and salt.
Add milk and cook over low heat until very thick.
Cool.
Add ham, onion and mustard. Chill overnight.
Shape into 12 small croquettes.
Roll in crumbs; dip in beaten egg, then in crumbs.
Fry in deep fat at 375°.

title: peach preserves
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a simmer stage.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Fill hot jars and seal.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Take pizza pan and grease entire pan, then press cookie dough on the pan as the crust. Bake cookie dough as it says on the pack. Then spread cream cheese over the cookie dough.
Then start to put the fruit on, one layer at a time.
Melt apple jelly and brush over the fruit for the glaze.
Refrigerate.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in glass pie plate.
Cover with chili, then cover with taco sauce.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: cheese dip
directions: Heat cream cheese for 2 minutes.
Mix in chili and chiles. Add 1/2 Cheddar cheese and heat another 3 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Pour on chips.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients in your serving dish and freeze. Remove approximately 20 minutes before serving.
Yummy!

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour over chicken wings.
Marinate overnight.
Bake 350 for 90 minutes.
Stir often.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack clean jars with okra.
Heat vinegar, water and salt. Bring to a rolling boil and pour over okra.
Seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: breakfast chocolate(chocolate pudding gravy)
directions: Combine milk, sugar and vanilla in a saucepan on medium heat. In a cup stir cocoa with about 1/2 cup of hot water; stir until smooth.
Pour into saucepan.
Continue to heat until boiling.
In a cup of hot water mix the cornstarch and pour into saucepan. Stir until thickened; eat with hot biscuits.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and serve cold.
Good with all raw vegetables.

title: "buddy's fruit salad"
directions: Slice bananas.
Rinse all fruit and pat dry.
In separate bowl, use hand mixer to mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sour cream.
Add all the fruit.
Add marshmallows and nuts; mix well. Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Yummie!!

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, eggs, buttermilk, soda and salt.
Add melted butter and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Batter should be very smooth before baking; add more milk if needed to reach this consistency.)
Serve with your dinner while still hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together and roll between waxed paper.
Makes 2 pie crusts.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in skillet.
Drain well.
Put browned hamburger and onions in crock-pot and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 16 hours.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Beat eggs; set aside.
Chop bacon and onion and fry.
Boil spaghetti.
Drain. Add butter and salt and pepper.
Pour bacon and onion over spaghetti; mix.
Pour eggs over spaghetti; mix.
Pour cream over spaghetti; mix.
Serve immediately.

title: mock peanut brittle
directions: Melt sugar and Karo syrup.
Add peanut butter and cornflakes. Mix.
Press into pan.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: *Cheddar, Mozzarella or Jack can be used.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Melt chips, milk and oleo on High in microwave-safe bowl for 3 to 4 minutes, until melted.
Add nuts and stir.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in the egg.
Add flour, sifted with soda; beat well.
Stir in nuts and potato chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: easy-do rolls
directions: Measure water into large mixer bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over water.
Add dry milk, sugar, oil, egg, salt and about 1 1/2 cups flour; blend well.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually add remaining flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover; let rest 15 minutes.
Toss dough on lightly floured surface until no longer sticky.
Knead 1 minute; shape.
Divide dough into 20 pieces.
Roll quickly into balls; place into greased pan.
Brush each with soft butter.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 20 rolls.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, it will be thick.
Mix it until all the ingredients are mixed smoothly together.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Bake in a Bundt cake pan.
Make sure you do not undercook it.

title: lion house chili
directions: Cover beans with cool water; soak overnight and cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce, tomato juice and seasonings.
Brown ground beef and onion in heavy skillet until lightly browned; drain of grease.
Add meat mixture to bean mixture; simmer 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
See below for alternative setting.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a large oblong pan, pour in your olive oil.
Place rinsed and dried chicken breasts in pan.
Cover breasts with tomato juice, plum tomatoes, onions, peppers, garlic and your spices.
Cover pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Halfway through the baking time, take pan out of oven to check if there is enough liquid in pan.
If not, add about 1/2 to 3/4 cup water.
Continue to bake until done and tender; enjoy!

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and beat until smooth and thick. Will keep well in refrigerator for a long time.

title: fruit filled layered angel dessert
directions: Bake and cool cake as directed on box.
Trim brown crust from cake.
Tear cake into about 1-inch pieces.
Prepare pudding as directed on box, using skim milk.
Fold in 2 cups whipped topping.

title: impossible taco pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a large pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inches).
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown.
Drain. Stir in taco mix.
Spread in plate.
Top with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth in blender or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on box, then mix juices.
Freeze. Crush with food chopper.
Put in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale. This goes over real well at weddings, etc.
You can also use as a crushed ice for the kids in the summer.

title: sinfully rich chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions and bake.
Let cake cool.
Poke holes in top of cake with handles of wooden spoon. Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake holes.
It will run down sides of cake.
Spread fudge topping over cake, then cover with Cool Whip.
Chop up Heath candy bars and sprinkle on top of cake.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Dissolve instant pudding in crushed pineapple and juice.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Place in a 9 x 11-inch dish. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cornstarch-gelatin finger paint
directions: In a small pan, add 3/4 cup cold water to cornstarch and stir into a smooth paste.
Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Pour 2 cups boiling water into the cornstarch paste, stirring constantly. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and is clear.
Remove from heat and stir in the dissolved gelatin.
Add food coloring or tempera paint for color.
Texture such as cornmeal, sawdust or coffee grounds may be added as desired.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Add milk. Pour on floured surface and knead.
Makes about 12.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a large greased skillet.
Top with mixture below.

title: hot dill pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, water and salt; bring to boil.
Slice cucumbers in strips and place into jars.
Add 1 teaspoon dill seed per quart and 1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper per quart.
Add garlic to taste.
Pour hot liquid into jars and seal.
Makes 8 or 9 quarts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli until tender.
Mix broccoli, margarine, soup and seasoning.
Mix in stuffing and 1/2 cheeses. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: no-cook eclair
directions: Mix sugar, milk and pudding.
Gradually add whipped topping.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Dump all ingredients in large bowl.
Mash it!
Knead it! Pound it!
The longer and harder you mix it, the better it tastes.
Roll dough into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Good dipped in chocolate.

title: fresh apple loaf
directions: Combine apples, pecans and sugar; mix well.
Let stand 1 hour, stirring often.
Do not drain.
Combine flour, soda, salt and spices in a large bowl.
Add apple mixture, stirring well.
Stir in butter, vanilla and eggs.
Spoon the batter into two greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans with 2-inch band of foil tied around the top of each can.
Or you can use two medium-size loaf pans. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes for coffee cans or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Bread baked in loaf pans should be done sooner.
Let cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove to complete cooling.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine flour, nuts and sugar in large bowl.
In separate bowl mix egg, milk, oil and bananas.
Combine both mixtures.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 350° until done.

title: banana bobs
directions: Cut bananas in 1 inch pieces. Put a popsicle stick in one end and freeze. After they are frozen, dip in chocolate and roll them in what ever you want.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix wafers, sugar, cocoa powder and nuts.
Stir in rum and syrup.
If necessary, add water to 1 to 1/4 teaspoon.
Form small balls.
Roll in powdered or granulated sugar.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Cook and drain broccoli. Combine broccoli, soup and cheese.
Stir in chicken and pour into a 2 quart casserole (preferably with a large surface area).
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 3.

title: lime cooler
directions: Combine concentrates with 8 cups water.
Add enough food coloring
to
make lime green. Chill thoroughly.
When ready to serve, add Sprite.

title: moon balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in cornflake crumbs. Refrigerate.

title: hi-energy pizza
directions: Boil turkey in a cup of water until brown.
Drain and set aside.
Line pizza pan with bread slices and sprinkle with Mrs. Dash.
Cook tomato supplement, 1/2 cup water, oregano, Mrs. Dash and thyme together until thickened.
Divide into four portions and spread over bread.
Cover each bread slice with 2 ounces ground turkey and sprinkle each with one ounce Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with onions, peppers and mushrooms.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: friendship cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; blend in eggs.
Add 2 cups flour and vanilla.
Dredge fruit (be sure it is well drained) in remaining flour.
Fold fruit and nuts into batter.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with your favorite chips or vegetables.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Be sure eggs are at room temperature.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Add salt and vanilla.
Fold in other ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop cookies by spoon onto ungreased foil-covered cookie sheet.
Place cookies in oven and immediately turn off oven.
Leave cookies in closed oven overnight.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Prepare a chocolate cake mix as directed and bake in a double sheet cake pan or 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jelly roll cake
directions: You will need at least a 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: argyle dressing
directions: Cream butter, salt and sugar.
Dissolve mustard in small amount of vinegar and add to the butter mixture with the egg yolks and remaining vinegar.
Cook in a double boiler until you're sure the egg yolks are done.
Add the marshmallows and stir to dissolve.
Chill.
Fold in the whipped cream and chopped nuts.

title: almond bars
directions: Mix the graham crackers and butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix the coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Put on top of crust.
Bake 15 minutes more. Frost with the almond bar and butterscotch chips.

title: old time bread pudding
directions: Put toast into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle raisins over toast.
Mix together eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, milk, water and vanilla.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with mixture of 4 teaspoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: seafood salad
directions: Blend Knox gelatine with 1 cup hot tomato soup (mixed according to directions on can).
Blend mayonnaise with cream cheese.
Stir into tomato mixture.
Add scant 1/2 teaspoon salt, sugar, chopped green pepper, celery and green onions.
After all the mixture is well mixed, gently fold in tuna, shrimp or crab or any combination.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in a small saucepan.
Add flour and mix well. Gradually add milk while stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Add pepper, onion powder and garlic powder.
Place potatoes and chopped onion
in a lightly oiled 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add sauce and mix.
Stir gently and bake, uncovered, an additional 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned and potatoes are tender.
Serves 5.
Contains 195 calories per serving.

title: magic bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate morsels, coconut and pecans; press down gently.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Loosely cover any leftovers.

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables as directed; drain and place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix cheese, celery, mayonnaise and onion together and spread over vegetables.

title: chicken breast with mushroom gravy
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add and brown chicken breasts. Spread mushrooms and mushroom soup over chicken breasts.
Cover skillet and cook on very low for 30 to 45 minutes.
(The longer you cook it, the more tender the chicken.) Check every 15 minutes or so and add small amount of water if sticking.
Good with rice.

title: holiday punch (green)
directions: Dissolve sugar and Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in lemon juice, then pineapple juice and cold water.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, onion, egg, cheese and soup.
Add cooked broccoli.
Cover with Ritz crackers and dot with butter.
Bake in casserole dish at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: potato fluff
directions: Spray casserole dish. Make potatoes and set aside. In 1 1/2 teaspoons oil, saute mushrooms, onion and garlic for 5 minutes. Put vegetables into bowl. Wipe skillet and heat remaining oil 4 minutes. Add turkey, soup, peas, broth and pepper. Mix well. Add mushrooms and onion. Put into casserole and spread potatoes on top, sealing edges. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tropical waldorf salad
directions: Combine bananas, apples, celery, dates and walnuts.

title: never fail cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately. Add extracts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Be sure your tube pan is a large one; this cake bakes high.

title: smothered liver and onions
directions: Place flour, pepper and regular salt in a large plastic container with lid.
(I use an empty gallon sherbet container that has been washed clean.)
Seal with lid on.
Shake ingredients up until they are thoroughly mixed.

title: red cabbage and apple slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and apple; set aside.
Combine vinegar and next 5 ingredients in a jar.
Add caraway seed; cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Drizzle over cabbage; toss gently.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve on red cabbage leaves.
Contains 1/4 g fat, o mg cholesterol and 99 mg sodium.

title: japanese fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas good. Add eggs and sugar; beat well. Mix baking soda with flour and add to mixture. Fold in nuts and lastly add melted butter. Pour into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan. Makes 1 loaf. Bake at 350° for 70 minutes. If you bake it in a glass dish, bake at 325°.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cover zucchini with boiling water.
Let set for 5 minutes. Drain and put into pie crust. Combine brown sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, sugar, salt, flour and lemon juice and pour over zucchini.
Dot with margarine and cover with top crust.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Tastes like apple pie.

title: buckwheat cakes
directions: Bake on hot griddle.
Save at least 1 cup of batter for your starter for your next batch of cakes.

title: fresh peach dessert
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in electric mixer about 5 minutes until light and fluffy.
Roll wafers or crackers into crumbs.
Spread half of crumbs in bottom of 12 x 8 x 2 inch pan.
Spread butter mixture over crumbs.
Put sliced peaches next.
Then whipped cream.
Add remaining crumbs. Refrigerate.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Mix milk with salad dressing; add to gelatin when cooled. Mix in the cottage cheese, carrots and onions.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk. Add coconut and lemon extract.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: stewed chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Cover with water.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook 1 hour on medium high, keeping water level above chicken.
Mix water and flour in a cup.
Pour in with chicken to thicken for gravy. Serve with rice.

title: fig preserves
directions: Put in enamel roaster.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 30 minutes with wooden spoon. Do not cover the roaster.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Add ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Juice of 1 lemon equals 2 to 3 tablespoons of lemon juice.

title: 30 minute cake
directions: Bring to a boil butter, cocoa and water.
While hot, add sugar and flour.
Stir well. Then add sour milk, soda, vanilla, cinnamon and beaten eggs.
Beat well.
Bake at 400° in a greased jelly roll pan until golden brown.

title: "speedie" roll dough
directions: Measure 3 1/4 cups
flour and sift.
Combine warm water, sugar and yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add salt and 1 cup flour.
Beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Add 1 egg and shortening. Beat 1 minute; work in remaining flour.
Cover and let rest 20 minutes.
Shape dough into desired shapes.
Place in greased pan. Cover; let rise in warm place 40 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.

title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk until well blended.
Add vanilla and Cool Whip; mix well.
(You may save 1/2 of Cool Whip for topping.) Layer wafers or crackers, bananas and pudding mix as you would any banana pudding.
Spread reserved whipped topping on top and chill.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Melt chocolate squares and set aside.
Cream butter and blend on high speed with sugar until creamy and smooth, approximately 9 minutes.
Beat until peaks form and texture is no longer grainy. Add chocolate square mixture to butter mixture and mix 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing on high speed for 3 to 5 minutes, after each egg.
Fold in Cool Whip until completely blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Shave candy bar on top.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Keep covered and refrigerated.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Allow cheese to soften at room temperature.
Cream cheese and all other ingredients together, except nuts.
(If pineapple is not completely drained, you will not be able to form a ball.)
Roll ball in the nuts; chill.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Melt stick of butter in skillet; add onions, mushrooms and salt.
Cook until onions are tender.
In a crock-pot, put thawed broccoli, cheese, onions, mushrooms and cream of mushroom soup. Cook on low until cheese is completely melted.
Wonderful as a dip or served over rice.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Brown chicken in butter and add celery, mushroom soup and water.
Pour over 1 package wild rice.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen avocado yogurt with candied lime strips
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl. Add first 3 ingredients.
Process until smooth, stopping occasionally to scrape down sides.
Pour into a large bowl. Add yogurt, stirring until blended.
Spoon mixture into an 8-inch square pan.
Cover and freeze. Top
each serving evenly with Candied Lime Strips. Yields 4 3/4 cups.

title: easy lemon poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat 30 seconds.
Spread in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Mix 2/3 cup powdered sugar and 3 to 4 teaspoons lemon juice until smooth.
Drizzle on cake.

title: toll oat cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt
butter. Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Add confectioners
sugar,
a
small
portion at a time. After mixing, roll
out in small balls.
Melt Candi-Quik. Dip balls in.
Lay
on aluminum foil.
Let stand for 45 minutes or until Candi-Quik has hardened.

title: mary lou's candy
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil, then time for 13 minutes. Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Continue to beat until mixed.
Pour into a butter dish.

title: shoestring salad
directions: Combine carrots, onions, celery and turkey or ham.
Toss with Miracle Whip and refrigerate.
Prior to serving, stir in potatoes. Serve on lettuce leaves or stuff a tomato.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken and debone; set aside.
Add rice to the same water that chicken was boiled in.
Cook until done.
Add soup and chicken.
Heat until soups are melted.

title: cheese paste for sandwiches
directions: Melt oleo on stove top in double boiler.
Add flour and mix well.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add hot milk and eggs. Stir while cooking until eggs are cooked, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add pimento.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine with garlic salt.
Mix other ingredients in large broiler pan.
Pour melted ingredients over all and mix. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring once or twice.

title: chocolate whipped cream
directions: In a deep bowl, use an electric mixer to beat together cream, sugar and cocoa until soft peaks form.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, vanilla and flour along with remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on lightly greased or sprayed baking sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake at 375° but watch closely.
These cookies burn easily.

title: frozen fluffy strawberry pie
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in toasted coconut.
Mix well.
Press in a 9-inch pie plate.
Chill in large bowl.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand milk.
Stir in strawberries and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into coconut crust mixture. Should mound slightly.
Freeze for 4 hours or until firm.
Before serving, garnish with fresh strawberries.
Return leftover to freezer.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and make large balls.
Put in baking dish.
Combine the last 4 ingredients together and pour over the ham balls.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Baste every 15 minutes.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Blend ingredients and serve with fruit.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add orange rind, yolks, orange juice and flour sifted with baking powder.
Mix well. Roll and cut into desired shapes.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: barry's dumplings and chicken
directions: Cover chicken with water and bring to boil.
Saute onions in oil.
Add onions, celery, carrot and bouillon cubes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Boil until chicken falls off bone.
Remove chicken from broth (save broth).
Let cool.
Remove chicken from bone and cube chicken and return to broth.
Bring chicken mixture to boil and add prepared dumplings.
Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Beat egg and milk together.
Add to dry ingredients and blend softly until mixed.
Put on floured board and roll to 1/8-inch thick and cut in finger size strips.
Drop into boiling mixture and reduce heat until just simmering and continue cooking for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not lift cover until the time is up.

title: sausage hots
directions: Remove skin from sausage.
Cook and crumble. Mix all ingredients and shape into small balls. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: First, cook spaghetti and set aside.
In a large pot combine both soups to a boil.
Then put in both packages of cream cheese and pimentos.
Cook until cream cheese is melted.
Add chicken. Then combine spaghetti to the soup mixture and add salt and pepper.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Bring to boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup and 2 cups milk.
Heat until done.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix following directions on box and bake. Mix pineapple and sugar in saucepan. Boil 5 minutes. Let cake cool, then spread pineapple over cake. Prepare pudding according to box. When set, pour over pineapple. Spread Cool Whip over pudding. Sprinkle nuts and coconut on top; refrigerate overnight. To add color, you can also garnish with maraschino cherries. For Christmas, use green and red.

title: beer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Put together oil, eggs and sugar; beat until light and fluffy, about 1 minute, on high.
Add flour, spices and baking soda; stir until mixed, then slowly put in beer while mixing until it blends.
Add nuts; mix.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Try with toothpick if ready.

title: unsweetened punch
directions: Mix in a gallon jar Kool-Aid and water.
Add sweetener and juice.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken and dressing scallop
directions: Saute celery and onion in small amount of butter.
Mix with dressing and spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Blend flour into broth.
Stir until thickened.
Mix small amount of hot mixture into eggs and return to broth.
Pour over chicken and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes, until firm.
Cool slightly.
Cut into squares and serve with Pimento Mushroom Sauce.

title: french toast
directions: Combine eggs (slightly beaten), milk and salt.
Dip day old bread into mixture.
Fry in small amount of hot grease until golden brown.
Serve with syrup or jelly.
Add sugar only if serving with syrup or jelly is not desired.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Put a layer of each ingredient (twice) in the order listed, in a punch bowl and refrigerate.
Should keep refrigerated until ready to serve and remainder refrigerated until eaten.

title: easy punch
directions: Pour fruit punch into large bowl. Add sugar; stir (be careful it may foam over). Add ginger ale and pineapple juice. Chill until ready to serve.

title: holiday tuna spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and tuna.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Place in mold (optional); refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or rye bread.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Bake in a 12 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix sugar, milk and 1/2 cup coconut.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat.

title: wagon wheel pasta with salsa chicken
directions: Cook pasta according to directions, omitting salt. While pasta cooks, combine salsa and chicken in a medium nonstick skillet. Cover and cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally. Place 1 cup drained pasta on each of 4 plates; top evenly with chicken mixture and cheese.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add all ingredients except cabbage. Simmer 5 minutes.
Place cabbage in greased 15 x 10 x 2-inch casserole.
Cover with meat mixture. Cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sugar. Combine baking powder with flour.
Add milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1
hour at 350°.

title: feta salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients.
For more liquid consistency, add some liquid from cheese or skim milk or dill pickle juice.

title: julie's birthday cake(chocolate-buttermilk cake)
directions: Bring to fast boil cocoa, butter, water and oil.
Add to combined sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs, soda, buttermilk, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 or 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: piccadillo
directions: Fry onions, peppers and garlic in 1/4 cup sweet oil until tender.
Add tomatoes and meat and stir with a fork to break up the pieces of meat.
Add salt and pepper, olives, raisins, capers and vinegar.
Cook slowly until meat is tender.

title: looed chicken wings
directions: Boil together all ingredients except sesame oil.
Simmer desired number of chicken wing pieces for 20 minutes. Cool in the liquid.
Serve cold with a bit of sesame oil on top.
Refrigerate and use sauce over and over. Replenish favorite flavors.

title: parrot pineapple salad boat
directions: Take the pineapple and cut it in half, all the way through the leaves (don't cut leaves off).
Then cut in half again.
Now, you should have 4 pieces with leaves on.
Cut out the core.
Slice between the pineapple and the outer covering, leaving fruit loose in shell.
Now, slice small cuts down into the pineapple and put slices of orange in.

title: salt-rising bread
directions: To 1 pint warm water, stir in flour to make a good batter.
Add salt.
Set in warm place for 6 to 8 hours.
Add flour and warm water or milk, and knead.
Rise and bake immediately.

title: philly steak sandwich
directions: Put the pepper and onions in frying pan with olive oil. Season, tenderize and cut up steak.
Fry in pan of butter; drain grease off meat.
Veggies go on top of meat.
Put the shredded cheese over top; cover to steam.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook, stirring constantly, over a medium heat, until it forms a ball.
It will be very stiff.
Lift out and knead well.
Keep in plastic bag.

title: beef and tortellini soup
directions: In a five quart Dutch oven, over high heat, cook beef, stirring frequently until well browned (about 10 minutes).
Spoon off fat.
Add tomatoes with puree (undiluted).
French onion soup, frozen green beans, tortellini, basil and 3 1/2 cups water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cover and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add zucchini.
Cook uncovered 10 minutes or until zucchini and tortellini are tender.
Makes about 11 cups.

title: fish and vegetable packets
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Place each fish fillet on a 12 inch square of aluminum foil. Top each fish fillet with one fourth of the vegetables. Sprinkle with dill weed, salt and pepper. Drizzle 1 Tbsp. chicken broth over each mound of vegetables. Fold up sides of foil to make a tent; fold top edges over to seal. Fold in sides, making a packet; fold to seal. Place packets on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 20 minutes or until vegetables are crisp tender and fish flakes easily with fork.
This has 7 grams carbohydrates.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Mix all ingredients together and spoon into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon on hot griddle.
If desired, mixture can be set in refrigerator overnight and cooked the next morning.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Boil shrimp and scallops for 5 minutes, until just cooked. Drain and let cool.
Cook tortellini until al dente; drain and let cool.
Combine olive oil, lemon juice, basil leaves, garlic and grated cheese in blender.
Toss ingredients together.
Add pepper to taste.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: dried fruit roll
directions: Grind all ingredients.
Add just enough juice to moisten. Roll in coconut.
Chill overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and add frosted flakes and butter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: nona's pasta salad *
directions: Brown sausages in a frypan with onion, peppers and garlic (use own fat, don't add oil).
Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Add rest of ingredients and chill.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: cherry salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together and refrigerate 2 hours or more.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Lightly oil a 12-cup fluted pan or mold.
In a large bowl, dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Chill until slightly set.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm. Unmold onto serving plate.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: oven baked rump roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With a sharp knife make 6 punctures in the roast and put 1 green onion, garlic clove and hot pepper in each hole.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over roast.
Pour the oil in a roaster pan and heat it on top of the stove over medium-high heat.
Sear the meat on all sides.
Pour in the wine and stock and sprinkle the chopped onions around the roast.
Cover the roaster, place it in the oven and bake for 2 hours or until desired doneness is reached.
Baste occasionally.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch dish; layer Doritos on top of chicken.
Melt butter and saute onion.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel and cheese.
Mix with onion and butter and pour over Doritos.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Blend well.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain. Pour all but 3 tablespoons drippings from saucepan.
Add onion and celery to drippings in pan.
Cook and stir until onion is tender. Remove from heat.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Put oil in skillet.
Brown pepper, onion and half the can of chiles.
Put in chicken and cook until done.
Dice chicken into chunks and set aside with vegetables.
Place chicken broth in saucepan and bring to a boil.

title: banana pudding mix
directions: Heat milk, sugar and salt.
Add cornstarch that has been mixed with a little of hot milk mixture.
Add to rest of mixture.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onions and pepper until tender and meat is crumbly.
When meat is brown add tomatoes and peas.
Remove from heat; drain some liquid off.
Add soup and set aside.
Cook noodles in salty water until tender.
Drain; add cream cheese cut in small pieces.
Add sour cream.
Put a layer of noodles and a layer of meat sauce until all is used.
Bake slowly at 300° for 30 or 40 minutes.
This recipe make a lot.
Use a large casserole dish.
This will keep a long time in the refrigerator.

title: cranberry-pineapple frozen salad
directions: Soften cheese and add ingredients in order given.
Pour into molds or paper muffin cups and freeze.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: cloud sponge cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks at high speed until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in water until pale and foamy. Gradually beat in sugar until completely dissolved, 8 to 10 minutes.
Add extract.
Fold flour mixture in three additions into yolk mixture.
Set aside.
In small mixer bowl with clean beaters, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Gently fold into batter.
Turn into ungreased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Invert pan to cool.
Use knife to loosen. Invert on plate.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Saute celery until soft; add onion and saute until soft.
In another bowl, add sauteed ingredients to bread crumbs (not necessary to toast).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel pecan rolls
directions: In bottom of deep dish baker or pie pan, mix brown sugar, melted butter and syrup together.
