On cutting board, spread crescent rolls out, two at a time, to form a rectangle.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place a line of chopped pecans down one end.
Roll up dough in a tube; cut into 5 pieces.
Place in baking dish, arranging over caramel mixture.
Place in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool for a few minutes before inverting onto serving plate so the caramel can set up and not run.

title: barb's guacamole layered dip
directions: *BLKLIN use 1 package dried avocado mix).

title: parmesan pocket bread appetizers
directions: Cut bread slices in half, then split each half.
Spread each bread half with about 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle with about 1 tablespoon of cheese and cut into 4 wedges.
Put wedge on a baking sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: cranberry-cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce.
Mix well and chill until thick, but not firm. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until set in 8-inch square pan. Cut into squares and serve on salad greens.

title: beet jelly
directions: Strain	beet juice after boiling until soft.
Boil beet juice, lemon
and pectin (Sure-Jell) for 1 minute.
Add sugar and jello; bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
The butter keeps the jelly from foaming.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo.
Add shrimp and cook on low heat until onion is transparent.
Turn off heat.
Add Worcestershire sauce and tomato sauce.
Mix into rice.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: aunt marie's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, soda and salt together in a medium bowl.
Set aside.
Cream the butter.
Add the brown sugar, vanilla and eggs; beat together in a large bowl.
(Using a hand mixer here is great!
If you have a Kitchenaide, wow!
But a wooden spoon works well, too!)
Add dry ingredients (a bit at a time) to the creamed mixture until well blended.
Fold in chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or so.
Cool on rack.

title: pasta primavera
directions: About 40 minutes before serving:
In saucepan, prepare spaghetti as directed.
Return to pan and keep warm.
In 2-quart saucepan on high heat in 1-inch boiling water, heat broccoli pieces to boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until tender-crisp; drain.

title: hot cashew-chicken salad
directions: Layer chips in bottom of casserole.
Combine other ingredients and place on top of chips.
Top with more crushed chips.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: german pizza
directions: In 12-inch skillet (regular or electric), over medium heat, brown the beef, onion, green pepper, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper. Remove meat mixture and drain off fat.

title: quiche
directions: Blend eggs, mustard, cream and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese in blender.
Cover bottom of cooked pie shells with Swiss cheese (1/2 cup).
Add liquid mixture.
Add meat or filling mixture.
Cover with remaining Swiss cheese and 1/2 cup of Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and chicken.
Spread in casserole dish; cover with crumbled Ritz crackers and pour melted butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in sherbet until ingredients are combined and mixture is smooth.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in orange segments and whipped cream.
Turn into 6-cup mold (1 1/2-quart) and chill until firm.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy pralines
directions: Mix all the ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring often.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil slowly for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from heat.
Beat until the candy begins to thicken, but still looks shiny.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Spread over casserole.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.
Serve warm topped with maple syrup.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Cook vegetables and add to gravy and turkey.
Pour into prepared pie shell and top with another pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Great for leftover Thanksgiving turkey.

title: berchie manley's famous bread pudding
directions: Combine crumbs, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and fat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Turn into greased baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven (350°).
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.
Serve with whipped cream (optional).
Nuts, raisins, etc. are optional.

title: easy mac & cheese
directions: Melt butter in 9 inch x 13 inch dish. Add uncooked macaroni, salt, pepper and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour milk over mixture, do not stir after adding milk.
Refrigerate overnight, or bake it right away.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour or until lightly browned.

title: blarney stones
directions: Cut cake in 1 1/2-inch slices.
Frost and cover with the peanuts.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour batter over nuts and coconut.
Mix together margarine and cream cheese.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Spread over top of the batter. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°; bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes and dump upside-down onto plate or cookie sheet.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Cut wieners into bite-size pieces, brown slightly in skillet. Put into barbecue sauce-apricot preserve mixture.

title: fast and fabulous fruit cup dessert
directions: Reserve small amount of drained fruit for garnish.
Combine pudding and fruit thoroughly.
Blend in Cool Whip until completely mixed.
Serve in nice glass dish (top with reserved fruit) to show off how delicious it looks!

title: reuben casserole
directions: Put sauerkraut in casserole.
Add crumbled corned beef, sliced tomatoes, cheese and Russian dressing.
Cube rye bread and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until cheese and bread brown.

title: sage beef dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a greased pan and bake until done.

title: coconut pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites and vinegar until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add nuts, coconut, crackers and baking powder.
Pour batter into 8-inch greased pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Top with whipped cream.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening (or oil); add salt and flour; mix well. Refrigerate for 15 minutes, then roll out and place into pie pans. Makes 4 (9 inch) pie crusts.

title: 24 hour refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers (if too large).
Place in a gallon jar along with dill and garlic.
Heat remaining ingredients but do not boil.
Let cool.

title: pear salad
directions: Toss with vinaigrette dressing.

title: cider cooked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Sprinkle inside and out with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Heat 1/2 the butter and all the oil in heavy skillet.
Add 1/2 the apples.
Saute 5 minutes, until browned.
Add ginger.
Stuff chicken with apples; tie or skewer chicken cavity closed.
Add remaining butter to pan. Brown chicken slowly on all sides.
Place chicken in heavy casserole with lid.
Add uncooked apples, green onions, thyme, cinnamon (if used), cloves and sugar to skillet.
Saute 2 minutes. Add cider; heat to boiling.
Pour over chicken.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together and pour on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Top will turn slightly brown colored.
Cool before cutting.

title: easy hamburg quiche
directions: Brown meat over medium heat; drain off fat.
Set aside. Blend next four ingredients until smooth; stir in meat, cheese, onion and pepper.
Turn into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and knife inserted comes clean. Serves 6.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts to taste.
Put in a casserole dish.
Flatten out.
Lay slice of cheese on chicken.
Mix soup with 1 can of water; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is well done.
Sprinkle dressing over top and bake for 10 to 15 minutes more.
Remove from oven and serve.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello and cream cheese in boiling water, mixing well or use an electric mixer.
Let stand until starts to jell.
Add crushed pineapple and pecans.
Let stand until starts to jell. Add Cool Whip.
Let stand until firm.

title: lemon chicken(4 servings)
directions: Cut each breast horizontally to make 2 slices; coat with flour.
Heat butter in skillet over medium heat.
Cook chicken and garlic in butter 4 to 6 minutes, turning once.
Add wine and lemon juice; sprinkle in pepper.
Heat until hot.

title: taco pizza
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and cottage cheese with mixer until well blended.
Spread on serving dish and chill.
Just prior to serving, top with taco sauce, onion, tomato, black olives and green pepper.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: garden soup
directions: Cook onions in melted butter until limp (5 minutes).
Add carrots and lettuce and cook, covered, over low heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add chicken broth.
Bring to boil.
Add rice.
Cook, covered, until rice is done and vegetables are very soft.
Puree in blender until smooth.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar on each bowl as you serve it and/or add a tablespoon of cream per serving.
(Can be halved, also can be frozen.)
Use hot or cold.

title: trout amandine
directions: Dip fillets in milk, season with salt and pepper then roll in flour so entire fillet is well coated.
Melt butter in skillet and cook fillets, browning evenly on both sides.
Remove fish from skillet.
In same skillet, add slivered almonds and saute. Sprinkle thickly over fish.

title: quick orange or lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix cake mix and orange or lemon Jell-O powder. Add vegetable oil and water and beat on medium speed 2 minutes. Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition. Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean. Remove from oven. Let stand 5 minutes. Turn out onto cake rack and allow to cool. Serve plain or sprinkle with powdered sugar. Makes 12 servings.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Heat soup, butter, and sour cream.
Break chicken into pieces in 9 inch x 13 inch casserole.	Pour heated soup mixture over chicken.	Spread crushed cracker crumbs and poppy seeds over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nut squares
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, flour and nuts. Mix well.
Spread into greased 9 x 12-inch baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: dad's favorite chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Add enough milk to make a paste.
Beat in egg yolks well.
Heat the sugar, flour, milk, cocoa and egg yolks until thickened.
When thick, take off heat and add vanilla.

title: chicken pie deluxe
directions: In bit kettle, put chicken and add water to cover.
Cook on medium for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken from kettle.
To broth, add the carrots, potatoes, celery and onion; cook for 15 minutes. Remove chicken from bones, cutting into pieces, and add to the broth.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Remove everything from broth and put in a large roaster.
Mix cornstarch and water to make gravy; add to chicken broth which is boiling.

title: caraway onion biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat together onions, eggs and oil. Combine flour, baking powder and caraway seed.
Combine dry and wet mixtures.

title: salad
directions: Let sugar, water, gelatin and pineapple boil about 5 minutes. Add cream cheese, Cool Whip and crushed nuts.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Chill and serve.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour and add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in oblong pan.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: In large bowl, combine dry cake mix, melted butter and eggs. Blend well.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13 baking pan.
Spoon pie filling evenly over batter.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in softened butter.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: delectable doo-dads
directions: Mix the flour, sugars, soda, salt and spices together in a large bowl.
Blend in Raisin Bran.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil; blend well.
Bake in paper muffin cups or greased tins for 15 minutes, or until done, at 400°.
Makes about 4 dozen muffins. This batter will keep 4 to 5 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: double chocolate mocha trifle
directions: Make brownies.
Cool & cut into 1 inch cubes.
Mix pudding mix & milk.
Dissolve coffee in water.
Add to pudding mixture.
Fold in whipped topping.
Mix well. layer brownies, pudding & toffee. Repeat.
Chill before serving.

title: fudge pie
directions: Grease a pie plate with oleo.
Dust with flour.
Pour in mixture and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top of pie will crack.
Don't overcook.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: chocolate chip wafer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheets with foil.
Lightly grease foil.
Cream butter and sugar in large bowl until light. Add egg; beat until creamy.
Stir in vanilla, flour and salt.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls 3-inches apart onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until edges are golden and centers are set.
(Cookies are soft when hot but become crispy as they cool.)
Cool completely on foil, then peel foil from cookies.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Heat one Coca-Cola to boiling.
Take off heat.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Then add the other Coca-Cola and remaining ingredients.
Place in refrigerator until gelled, about 2 hours.
Put in Pyrex dish; cut in squares.

title: sausage loaf
directions: Mix sausage and bread crumbs.
Add onion, ketchup, horseradish, mustard, and egg moisten with milk.
Shape into loaf. Bake at 350 for 1 hour.

title: hot delights
directions: Mix together. Spread on party rye and bake at 350 degrees until bubbly. Enjoy!

title: chocolate covered cherry-ettes
directions: Sift together sifted flour and salt.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sifted confectioners sugar, creaming well.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Beat well.
Blend in the dry ingredients, nuts and well drained maraschino cherries.
Shape dough into balls, using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Dip in Chocolate Glaze.
Let stand on rack until chocolate hardens (2 to 3 hours).

title: upside-down sausage cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook
sausage,
onion
and green pepper until sausage is
brown
and
crumbly.
Stir
in flour. Mix in tomato paste, chili
powder,
salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese and olives.
Spread
evenly
in
a
greased and floured 9-inch pan. Prepare mix
to
package directions.
Spread over sausage mixture. Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done.
Let stand 5 minutes, loosen edges.
Invert onto plate. Serve immediately.

title: beet salad
directions: Prepare Italian dressing according to directions.
Drain the sliced beets; place in glass dish. Marinate beets in Italian dressing in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Separate lettuce into leaves and place on salad plate.
Place several beet slices on each lettuce leaf.
Place one onion slice on top.
Spoon dressing over onion and beets.
Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Add carrots and nuts. Bake at 350°.
You may add 1/2 cup raisins or chopped dates.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Pour the boiling water over rice and let stand for 15 to 20 minutes; drain. Place rice in 3-quart casserole (spray with Pam). Add the soups, mushrooms, celery, onions, seasonings and bouillon. Brown meat well. Add half of the almonds. Mix all together and sprinkle remainder of the almonds on the top. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or a little longer. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon.
Boil for 5 more minutes.
Take off heat and quickly add vanilla and baking soda.
Fold in popped corn, mixing well.
Bake on cookie sheet for 30 to 40 minutes at 250° , stirring every 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: raspberry jelly
directions: Mash green tomatoes. Add sugar. Mix well. Bring to boil. Boil 30 minutes. (Stir so sugar will not stick to pan.) Add Jell-O. Mix well. Boil 7 minutes more. Pour in sterilized jars. Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: layered jello
directions: Mix 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each flavor Jell-O.
Cool in separate bowls.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until it tests done.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Sprinkle with the nuts. Very easy and tastes great!

title: banana cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Blend in butter, 1/2 cup buttermilk and mashed bananas.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining buttermilk.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and place cake on serving platter.
Spread the butter frosting on top and sides of the cake.

title: garden pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill or eat warm.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a deep fryer, heat vegetable oil to 365°.
In large mixing bowl, combine all other ingredients; blend well.
Shape batter into small balls, approximately 1 tablespoon each.
Use a long handle spoon to slide balls into the oil.
Cook hush puppies, 8 or 10 at a time, until brown.
Remove from the oil with a slotted spoon.
Roll on paper towels until drained.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring to a boil the water, sugar and cranberries.
Boil until they pop.
Add cherry jello and cool slightly.
Add crushed pineapple, cut up grapes and chopped nuts.

title: green bean casserole lite
directions: Saute onion.
Pour soup into a quart casserole dish.
Add sauteed onion, green beans, mushroom pieces and pepper. Mix well. Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix with 1 cup hot water.
Add one small can crushed pineapple.
Add chopped celery and nuts.
Let set.

title: mai tai
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in tall glass containing ice.
Serve with pineapple spear, sprig of mint and a straw.
Yield: 1 serving.

title: spicy tomato soup with crudites
directions: Combine the tomato juice, onion, celery seed, hot pepper and Worcestershire sauce in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 7 to 10 minutes, or until heated through.
If you wish, the same mixture can be poured into 4 mugs, covered and heated for the same amount of time.
Serve the soup with the celery sticks, radishes and cucumber sticks.

title: green jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix cottage cheese and jello.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: gobbler turkey
directions: You will need 1 ice cream scooper.

title: d c beans
directions: Place onion and beef in pot; brown.
Add onion salt, garlic salt, beans and sausage.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 30 minutes. Serve topped with green onions and grated cheese.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light. Add eggs, mashed bananas, pecans and buttermilk. Mix dry ingredients and add to banana mixture. Pour into a greased Bundt pan or a 9 x 13 baking pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. When cool, frost with Banana Nut Icing.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with canned biscuits. Bake at 400° until biscuits are brown.

title: egg pastry
directions: Sift together flour and salt and cut in shortening.
Beat egg slightly.
Add vinegar and water.
Add gradually to dry ingredients.
Work just enough to hold together for pie.
Work more for dumplings.
Roll and cut.

title: special shrimp mold
directions: Melt gelatin in water over low heat.
Add soup and cream cheese; heat until smooth.
Add celery, onion and shrimp; heat again.
Add mayo, salt and pepper.
Spray ring mold with Pam. Pour mixture into mold and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 30.

title: peanut butter-chocolate chip balls
directions: Put powdered sugar in a bowl.
Add chocolate chips.
Add condensed milk.
Add crunchy peanut butter. Mix well.
Drop candy from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
May sprinkle or roll in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate.

title: possum and sweet taters
directions: Pour
a
large	kettleful
of hot water in a convenient vessel,
add
a
small shovel of ashes, then put the possum in this.
Do
not have the water as hot as for scalding chickens. Turn the possum around until the skin is loosened and you will have no trouble in skinning him perfectly clean.
Remove head, feet
and
entrails.
Wash	thoroughly in cold water.
Salt in and outside and let hang overnight.

title: chocolate mousse cheesecake
directions: Combine
the
crumbs
from
both
mixes
for the crust. Spread evenly along bottom and sides of pan.
Prepare cheesecake following
directions
on box.
Spread evenly over crust and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Prepare chocolate mousse following directions on box.
Spread evenly over chilled cheesecake. Shave chocolate
bar
over
top of mousse.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: frozen yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into whipped topping, blending well. Add fruit. Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes (or longer, for softer texture) before cutting and keep chilled in refrigerator.
Garnish with fruit, if desired. Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Place on greased pan.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper seasoning, paprika, garlic salt and pepper.
Bake in covered or uncovered dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: famous stew
directions: In a separate bowl, cover with butter, lots of season salt, pepper.
Put one cup of water over potatoes, cover dish and microwave 20 minutes, stir, then 10 minutes more until done.
Add potatoes and juice to stew pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on stove for at least 30 minutes, or simmer as long as needed. Goes great with cheese on top and cornbread.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with Fritos.
Do not reheat leftover dip.

title: coated pecans
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream and syrup in saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss. Add nuts quickly and stir until covered.
Spread onto foil and break apart when cool into pieces.

title: tea scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in margarine with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine bread crumbs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with fork. Divide into 2 parts and turn each part out on floured board. Do not handle.
Flatten with rolling pin into circles about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into shapes with cookie cutters. Put on greased and floured cookie sheet.

title: tangy short ribs
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Combine all other ingredients and place in 5-quart Dutch oven.
Place ribs, meaty side up, atop mixture.
Bake, covered, for 3 hours at 350°.
Baste meat with juice several times during the last hour of cooking.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream together.
Spread half the mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix together the brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over the batter in pan. Spread rest of cake batter on top, then rest of sugar mixture. Swirl with knife.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: red hots
directions: Soak cucumber slices in lime and water for 24 hours.
Wash and soak in ice water for 3 hours.
Mix 1 cup vinegar, alum and water to cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Pour off liquid.

title: hot cider wine
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil in a large heavy pan and simmer 1 hour.

title: south of the border chicken
directions: Boil chicken, debone and cut in bite size pieces.
Heat milk, soup and salt and pepper to taste.
Cool.
When cool, add some onion, tortillas, chicken, sauce and grated cheese, saving some cheese for top.
Place in casserole; let stand for several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: russian rye dill dip
directions: Cut out center of loaf and cube bread for dipping.
Mix all remaining ingredients together.
Place inside hollowed-out loaf of bread.
Raw vegetables are also good for dipping.

title: aunt b's yeast rolls
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Blend yeast and warm water and add to creamed mixture.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time. Spray 12-hole muffin tin (even the top) with Pam.
Fill muffin cups to top with batter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pastry for small pies
directions: Mix with fork all ingredients.	Form a ball.
Pinch off in small balls and roll out thin.
For small pies, you may use peach preserves, cherry preserves or
your
own cooked fruits. This pastry may be stored in refrigerator until needed.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until blended.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle cheese on top.
Spread with mushrooms and sprinkle with crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir flour, salt, sugar and butter into corn.
Add well beaten eggs to milk; stir into corn mixture.
Place in a 2 quart lightly buttered shallow baking dish.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 325°. Stir from the bottom (3 times), during baking time.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks and mix.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Beat well together. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and nuts.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375° in a 9-inch cake pan.

title: spanish style goulash
directions: Take 1 (9-inch) skillet or medium saucepan.
Prepare ground beef with at least 1 cup water (keeps from burning; also soft) with chopped onions.
Add chopped tomatoes.
Cook slowly until brown.
Add chili powder and salt.
If needed, add more water for macaroni.
When macaroni is done, top with corn chips and cheese. One pan, one clean up.

title: chicken curry
directions: Saute garlic, onions and tomatoes in frypan.
Add chicken pieces.
Cook until brown and add sour cream or coconut milk.
Add water to make substance.
Add curry powder and salt.
Cook until done.
May add 4 Doritos green chiles, if desired (optional).
For best results, cook in crock-pot.

title: microwave cinnamon apples
directions: Quarter, core and peel apples. Thinly slice apples into the baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and lemon juice.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 15 to 18 minutes.
Let sit about 5 minutes.
Uncover and serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: imitation crab salad
directions: Mix crab, celery, onion and pimiento with just enough mayonnaise to completely moisten.
Add lemon-pepper seasoning and lemon juice to taste.
Allow to sit, covered, in the refrigerator at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve over a bed of lettuce with tomato wedges and fruit garnish for a super-refreshing lunch!

title: easy coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onions and carrot and mix well.
In separate bowl, combine mayonnaise and relish.
Pour dressing over vegetables, cover and refrigerate overnight to enhance flavor.

title: cherry or blueberry "yum yum"
directions: Make graham cracker crust from graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Pat firmly onto a cookie sheet.
Spread pie filling on crust.
Whip together the Cool Whip and cream cheese; spread on top of pie filling.
Chill for 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: mama's sugar syrup
directions: Caramelize 1/2 cup sugar in large iron skillet, stirring so it won't burn.
Pour in 4 cups boiling water and rest of sugar; boil for 12 minutes.
Can be poured into clean hot jars and sealed. May be kept to use as needed.
While hot, pour over buttered biscuits!
It's great.

title: velveeta cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Place in crock-pot.
Cut up block of Velveeta cheese and place in crock-pot along with jar of salsa. Cook on high until good and melted while adding a little milk to help.
Serve with corn chips.

title: french bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, oil and 3 cups flour.
Beat vigorously for 2 to 3 minutes.
Sift in enough additional flour to make dough stiff. Allow dough to rest 10 minutes.
Add flour as needed, knead and allow to rest, four more times.
Grease 2 large baking sheets, sprinkle with cornmeal and set aside.
Divide dough in two.
Roll each into a 12 x 9 inch rectangle, then roll like a jelly roll. Pinch to seal.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Make 3 slits across the top. Brush with egg.
Bake 25 - 30 minutes at 400° or until brown. Makes 2 loaves.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour with baking powder.
Mix well but not overbeat.
Pour into a tube pan which has been well-greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in bowl for microwave.
Add milk. Dissolve and microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add beaten egg.
Stir in well.
Return to microwave for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Return to microwave (Medium heat) for 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened.
Stir and put over layer of bananas and vanilla wafers, repeating until each layer is covered.

title: frosty orange cooler
directions: In a pitcher, combine water, juices and sugar. Stir well until sugar dissolves. Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and scoop sherbet into glasses.
Pour in juice mixture and garnish as desired.

title: chinese pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from chops; heat one piece in large skillet until pan is greased, then saute chops until browned on both sides, remove chops, turn down heat.

title: fried pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper each chop, allowing to set for 10 minutes. Beat eggs and milk.
Dip each chop in milk mixture and roll in bread crumbs.
Brown slowly in hot grease, turning only one time. Remove from pan.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix squash, onion and pepper.
Cover with salt, mix well and let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Pour over squash mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Fill hot jars to 1/2-inch from top.
Adjust lids and process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in loaf pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Crust Layer:
Mix flour and margarine together like pie dough. Add pecans.
Spread into 9 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: mom-mom's fruit cake
directions: Wash raisins and cook with cider and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add butter and set aside to cool. Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices together.
Cut up nuts and fruit and add to the flour mixture. Beat eggs fluffy, then add the raisins, then add flour.
Beat to mix well.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
